Recipe: For the recipe for Fresh Beans with Olive Oil; Fry the diced onion with 1 tablespoon of olive oil, which we started to heat in a saucepan. Add the green beans to the onions that are starting to turn colors, and add sugar and salt to it. Add black pepper if desired. After making sure that the onions and beans are well mixed, scatter coarsely chopped tomato slices over the beans. After adding enough water to fill the bottom of the pot, close the lid and let it cook. Fresh Beans with Olive Oil is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.
To prepare a meaty dish; cubed meat is put in a pot

For the chicken dish with vegetables; Put the vegetable oil, chopped onion and pepper in the pot. After sautéing for a while, add the diced chicken breast. Keep sautéing until the chicken changes color. Then add the carrots and cook. Add the diced potatoes and continue cooking. After putting the tomato paste, tomato and peas in the pot, add the garlic, salt, black pepper and paprika. Cook on medium heat. Chicken with vegetables is ready to serve. Good luck :)

For the eggplant moussaka; Chop the onions and cook them with oil. Add the minced meat and after frying, add the eggplant, pepper, tomato and garlic. Add salt, pepper and cook on medium heat until the eggplants are soft. Tip; After dicing the eggplants, soak them in lemon and salted water for 20-30 minutes. Before putting them in the pot, pour the salted lemon water and wash the eggplants and throw them in the pot. Eggplant moussaka is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the red lentil soup; wash the lentils. Bring the lentils to a boil in a saucepan with water. Finely chop the onion, peel and grate the carrot. Add the onion, carrot and salt you prepared to the boiling mixture and cook for about 30 minutes. You can take the soup from the fire and strain it as desired, or you can put it back on the fire after passing it through the blender. Then fry the oil and flour in the pan until it turns slightly yellow, add the tomato paste and fry a little more, then add a few spoons of the soup into it, mash and mix it into the soup. Stir until boiling, cook for another 5 minutes and your lentil soup will be ready. Enjoy your meal :)

For the vegetable meat saute recipe; Finely chop the meat and put it in the pot. Cook on the stove for about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the water is absorbed. Peel the onion and finely chop it. Wash other vegetables as well. Separate the stems and seeds of the pepper, extract the dill. Finely chop the pepper and dill. Finely dice the tomato. Add the pepper and onion to the meat and fry for 1-2 minutes. Mix the tomatoes, dill, salt and spices, cover the pot and cook for another 20 minutes. Meat sauteed with vegetables is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For stuffed peppers with meat; wash the peppers. Cut off your stems. Cut off the top of the peppers without cutting them off completely. Take out your seeds. To prepare the inside; Grate the tomatoes, onions, wash the parsley and rice, finely chop the parsley. Put the onion and tomato grater in a bowl. Add the minced meat and the rice you have cleaned and washed to the bowl and mix well. As you're ready, stuff the bell peppers and place them in the pot. Mix the water, oil and salt in a bowl and pour it over the stuffed stuff you lined up. Cook on low fire until the rice swells. Stuffed peppers with meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the zucchini with cheese in the oven; After sorting and peeling the zucchini, boil them whole in salted water (alive) for 5 minutes and remove from the pot. Whisk together the curd cheese, finely chopped dill, olive oil and raw egg to mash. Cut the zucchini in half lengthwise and place them in the baking dish. Empty the middle with the help of a small spoon and fill the pits with the cheese mortar you prepared. Cover it with grated cheese and bake in a preheated oven at 160 degrees until the cheese melts (approximately 10-12 minutes). You can serve the zucchini with cheese in the oven hot. Enjoy your meal.

For the broccoli soup; Separate the florets of broccoli, wash it in plenty of water and chop it into small pieces. Grate the onion, dice the potato. Add the oil and the broccoli you washed and chopped, the onion you grated and the potato you cut into the pan. Cook by mixing beer. Then add 3 cups of water and let it boil. When the vegetables are cooked, take them off the stove and mix them with a blender until you get a homogeneous mixture. Add milk and cream to it and mix well. Put it back on the stove, cook for 5 more minutes after boiling and add salt and pepper and take it off the stove. Milk broccoli soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the creamless pumpkin soup; Preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Slice and grease half of a small pumpkin, then place it on the baking tray. Bake the pumpkin in the oven until it is soft and can be mashed with a fork. Saute the onion and olive oil in a medium saucepan until the onions turn yellow. Add the zucchini, salt and pepper that you took out of the oven to this mixture. Then slowly add 2 cups of chicken or vegetable broth to this mixture and cook for 5-10 minutes after boiling. Make sure your soup is a thick thick soup. If desired, you can crush it with a blender. You can serve the creamless pumpkin soup by garnishing it with walnuts or parsley. Enjoy your meal :)

For eight squash soup; First, grate the onion and garlic. After sautéing with oil for 5 minutes, you can add the grated zucchini to the pot. Fry the mixture for another 5 minutes and add hot water and leave the soup to cook. In a separate bowl, whisk the yogurt and flour with half a glass of water. After you finish the whisking process, add 1 cup of hot water to ensure that the seasoning is not interrupted. Now you can pour the yogurt slowly over your cooking soup. When your soup starts to boil, make sure it has the right consistency and add salt. If you want, you can add finely chopped dill and chili pepper to your soup. Pumpkin Soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the vegetable lentil soup recipe; Boil the lentils in a small amount of water. After straining, add the chopped vegetables and lentils to the pot and boil them again in 4 glasses of water. After the mixture is cooked, pass it through the mixer and add 2 glasses of hot water, then oil, cumin, salt and beef bouillon into the soup. After boiling until it reaches a sufficient consistency, green lentil soup with vegetables is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the zucchini with minced meat; Dice the onions and fry them in oil until they turn pink. After the onions are browned, add the minced meat. Then add the diced tomatoes and chopped peppers. Put the paste and add the chopped zucchini to the pot. If you want, you can also add salt, pepper and garlic to your food. Finally, add 1 cup of hot water. Zucchini with minced meat is ready to be served after boiling. Enjoy your meal :)

For the cauliflower moussaka recipe; Cut off the root of the cauliflower and divide into the sizes you want. After boiling the cut pieces in boiling water for 2-3 minutes, drain them. Fry the onions in oil until golden brown and add the minced meat. Add the diced tomatoes and garlic to the mix. After adding tomato paste, salt and chili peppers, cook for 5 more minutes and pour the boiled cauliflower into the pot. Add 2 more glasses of hot water and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes. Cauliflower moussaka is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal!

For the anchovy sardine salad; After adding enough vinegar to cover the sardine fish, the scales of which have been cleaned, in a deep plate, it is left for one hour. Then, the fish are removed from the vinegar and the bones are removed by dividing them in half lengthwise. The fillets are arranged in a round shape, half an inch apart, in the middle of a large, round plate. It is put into the boiling water once and removed, and the peeled and chopped tomatoes are put into rings or a boiled egg cut into rings in an egg cutter. The salad is decorated by placing half-seeded olives on them. Vinegar and olive oil are whisked in a bowl and served on the sardines on the plate. Enjoy your meal :)

To prepare the bechamel sauce; Melt the butter in the pan, add the flour and fry for 2-3 minutes. Put the onion in the milk and bring to a boil. Take out the onion and slowly add the milk to the butter and flour mixture you roasted. Add salt, black pepper and boil it until it reaches the desired consistency. Béchamel sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the stuffing of Stuffed Peppers with Olive Oil; Chop the onion very finely. Sort the rice and wash it thoroughly until the white water does not flow. Put the currants in a bowl and add boiling water to it. They will both soften and swell, and dirt and garbage will accumulate on the bottom, so before using, remove the currants from the bowl, trying not to get them from the bottom. Rinse it one more time. Put the olive oil in the pan. When it's hot, add the pine nuts. Add the finely chopped onions, which are almost pink, and fry them until they become transparent. Then add the rice, all the spices, currants and water and mix. Cook the stuffing until the rice absorbs its water. Stuff the green bell peppers with the mortar, not too tightly. As a cover, you can use pieces of tomato. Lay the stuffing upright in the pan. Pour a mixture of boiling water and olive oil over it as cooking water. Cook, checking the water frequently. When the water is finished, add a little boiling water to the pot. Stuffed Peppers with Olive Oil is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the chocolate pie; 1.5 cups of milk is boiled. Mix the remaining half glass of milk with sugar, starch and cocoa until smooth. This mixture is added to the boiling milk little by little by mixing. 2-3 min. cooked and removed from the stove. If desired, crushed chocolate can be added at this stage and mixed. Allow to cool, stirring occasionally. In a separate place, soft butter is mixed with sugar. Add eggs, milk and cocoa and continue mixing. Finally, flour, cocoa and baking powder are added. Half of this mixture is poured into a greased springform mold. Pour the cooled cocoa sauce on it and spread it without getting too close to the edges. The remaining mixture is poured on top and smoothed out with a spoon. 20-30 minutes in the oven heated to 180 degrees. is cooked. After the chocolate pie comes out of the oven, it is turned upside down on a serving plate and decorated with powdered sugar. Enjoy your meal :)

For the strawberry jam recipe; Wash the strawberries several times. Cut off the stems, put the strawberries in a deep pot and pour 4 cups of granulated sugar over them. Close the lid of the pot and leave it in this state for 1.5-2 days. After waiting, put the pot on medium heat and boil the jam for about 40-45 minutes. After making jam, add lemon juice and boil for 1-2 more times. Remove the foams that have formed with a colander. Transfer the strawberry jam to glass jars and cool. Pour it into the bowl when you use it. Strawberry jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Dill Rice recipe; Wash the rice with plenty of water, then soak the rice in salted water for a while. Put the butter and oil in a saucepan and melt the butter over low heat. After adding the rice, add salt while the rice is roasting, fry for 5 minutes, add the water and cook with the lid closed until the water is gone. Finely chop the dill and add it to the rice and mix it a few times. Cover it with a paper towel and let it rest for a while. Dill Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the tomato soup; Slightly fry 2 tablespoons of flour with 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Add 5 grated tomatoes with 1 tablespoon of tomato paste. If it clumps, mix it with a hand blender at this stage. Then add 5 glasses of water. Cook stirring until thickened. While serving, add milk and salt to the pot. Tomato soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the tomato pasta; grate the tomatoes and crush the garlic. Melt the oil in a saucepan. Add the garlic and tomatoes and add some salt. When it is cooked a little, add the tomato paste. After cooking for a while, add the crushed flour in a little water. Boil the pasta in salted water and strain it. Strainer Wash it once with cold water and drain it. You can pour it over the pasta and serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the tomato rice; The skins of the tomatoes are peeled and fried with olive oil. Pre-soaked rice is added to the softened tomatoes and the roasting process is continued. Add boiling water, sugar and salt to the roasted rice and reduce the heat to the bottom of the stove. Enjoy your meal :)

For okra with diced meat; Wash the okra in plenty of water and put it in a strainer. Take the finely chopped onion, two spoons of vegetable oil and the washed meat in a saucepan and put it on the stove. Stir occasionally and cook lightly until the water evaporates. Add half of the peeled, seeds removed and finely chopped tomatoes to the meat. .After 5 minutes, add 3-4 cups of hot water and salt and cook on low heat. Peel the tops of the okra in a cone shape and sort out. Add it to the meat with the remaining tomatoes. Add a little more hot water if necessary and squeeze 1/2 lemon. cook until. Okra with cubed meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the stuffed zucchini; Soak the rice in boiling water with a teaspoon of salt for 15 minutes and drain. Peel and chop the onion. Clean and chop the dill. Peel the zucchini variegated. Cut them one inch thick and remove the insides. Cut the zucchini insides into dice and put them in a bowl. Add onion, minced meat, dill, tomato paste, a tea glass of water, butter, salt and knead. Finally, add the rice and mix with a wooden spoon. Divide the stuffing you prepared into the zucchini. To cover them, cut the tomatoes large enough to cover the zucchini. Place the tomatoes as a lid and place them in the pot. Add two teaspoons of water from the rim of the pot. When it boils, cook on low heat until the zucchini is soft. Stuffed zucchini with meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the meaty cabbage wrap; First, separate the leaves of the cabbage without tearing it. Wash it, throw it into boiling salted water, 1-2 at a time, close the lid of the pot and boil for 1-2 minutes. Take it out with the slotted ladle, set it aside and finish all the cabbages like this. Separate the leaves from the veined parts so that they can be wrapped. For the mortar, add tomato paste, rice, minced meat, salt and pepper to the grated onion and mix well. Sprinkle with mint and pour half a cup of cabbage boiling water into it. Place the hard parts of the cabbage at the bottom of a flat pot. Open the cabbage leaves into the palm of your hand, put some of the mortar you prepared and wrap them. Sort it into the pot, put enough water on it and close the lid. Cook until the cabbages and rice are tender. Cabbage wrap with meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For succulent leaf wrap; Soak the pickled vine leaves in boiling water for half an hour. Cut off the stems of each before wrapping. For the stuffing, mix all the ingredients except the leaf. Chop the onion and garlic very finely while adding them. First, spread the leaf on the plate with the matte part of the leaf facing you: According to the size of the leaf, put about one teaspoonful of the stuffing in the corner of the leaf. Try to give the leaf's edges a slightly inward curl to give it a filling shape. Wrap all the leaves in this way. Fleshy leaf wraps Cover the bottom of the pan with torn or deformed leaves and stems. Put 1 teaspoon of pepper paste, tomato paste and olive oil required for cooking water in a small saucepan or saucer. Boil the tomato paste until it melts and pour it over the wraps. Cover the stuffing with a plate suitable for the size of your pan. While the stuffing is cooking, make sure to check its water from time to time. If it has run out of water, add boiling water to the pot. You can serve it with or without yogurt. Meat wraps are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the tripe soup; Rinse the cleaned tripe with plenty of water. Take it in a pot and add enough water to get three fingers on it, add the juice of half a lemon and chopped garlic and boil the tripe until it softens. Take the cooked tripe out with a slotted ladle and chop it into cubes of sugar. Pass the water of the tripe through a strainer, put it in another pot and let it boil. For its dressing, add the juice of one lemon, two egg yolks and 1-2 cups of water to two spoons of flour and whisk until smooth and lump-free. Pour in the boiling tripe water little by little and stirring constantly. Add the chopped tripe, adjust the salt and boil for 5 minutes. Add the crushed garlic. Then cook the chili peppers in butter for the sauce. Tripe soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the cheddar spinach recipe; Wash the spinach thoroughly and chop coarsely. Peel the onion and chop finely. Heat the oil in the pan and start frying the onion. Add the washed and drained spinach, salt, pepper and rice that you rinsed and drained thoroughly to the roasted onions and cook until the spinach releases its water and recedes. Take the cooked spinach in a glass bowl and sprinkle grated cheddar cheese on it. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven until the cheeses melt. Spinach with cheddar is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the cheddar cheese omelet recipe; Crack the eggs into a bowl, add parsley, salt, pepper and grated cheddar and whisk. Put the oil in a pan, add the whipped mixture when it gets hot and cook it to the consistency you want. When taking it to the serving plate, you can fold it from both sides towards the middle, then fold it in half and take it to the serving plate. Cheddar cheese omelet is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the wholemeal cookies recipe; Sift 1 cup of bran flour and half a cup of flour together with baking powder. Add cocoa and salt to it and mix with the help of a spoon. In a separate bowl, beat butter, oil, eggs, granulated sugar and vanilla sugar with a mixer for 2-3 minutes. Add the flour mixture and beat for 1 more minute on low speed. Add the hazelnuts and mix with a spoon. Take one teaspoon of the dough and with the help of a second spoon, arrange the dough on a greased or baking paper lined baking tray at intervals and bake. Whole wheat cookies are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the meaty winter type; Chop the onions into small cubes. Melt the margarine in a saucepan and add the onion and meat. Roast for about 20 minutes until the meat releases its juices and absorbs again. Add hot water and salt and cook with the lid closed for half an hour. Clean the leeks and chop them half-finger thick. Slice the celery into half moons. Cut the carrots and potatoes into cubes. Add the chopped leek, celery, carrot, potato and garlic to the meat and cook for another half an hour on low heat. Meaty winter kind is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the minced artichokes; Boil the artichokes in lemon and slightly salted water for 15 minutes. The water should be just above the artichokes. Add 1/2 tablespoon of flour to the water. Drain the artichokes and separate the boiling water. Fry the onion with olive oil. Add the minced meat and fry some more. Cut a lid off 6 tomatoes and take out the insides of the tomatoes. Chop the seedless part of the inside of a tomato and add the mince mix. Add salt and cook the minced meat for 10 minutes. Fill the cooked minced meat into the hollowed-out tomatoes. Cover the artichokes over the tomatoes, turn them upside down and place them in an oven dish with the artichoke side down. Pour the boiling water of the artichoke into my debt. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 20 minutes. Minced artichoke is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Fresh Beans recipe with Minced Meat; After breaking the ends of the beans, cut them in half lengthwise with a sharp knife. Peel the onion and chop finely. Transfer the olive oil and minced meat to a medium-sized large saucepan and fry for 2 minutes on medium heat until it gives its own juice and absorbs it. Add the chopped onions and tomato paste and fry for 2-3 more minutes. Add the beans, add salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally, until the beans turn green. Add hot water and cook on medium heat until it boils. When it starts to boil, lower the stove and wait until the beans are soft. Green beans with minced meat are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

To make purslane with minced meat, first cut the root parts of the purslane, extract it and wash it thoroughly in plenty of water. After peeling the onion, finely chop it. Then heat the oil in the pan and start frying the onion. Add the ground beef and continue frying before the onions turn pink. Chop the peeled tomatoes into cubes. Wash the rice and drain the water. When the ground beef is roasted, add 1 glass of water, salt, pepper, tomato, rice and purslane and cook on low heat. Purslane with minced meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal!

For the diced chicken potatoes; Chop the chicken in cubes, add sunflower oil and the chopped chicken to the pan and fry it until it is slightly juicy. Add the finely chopped green peppers, red peppers and onions to the chicken and mix well. 5 min. Cook with the lid closed throughout. After five minutes, add the tomatoes and diced potatoes. Dissolve the spices in half a glass of water, add them to the chopped tomatoes, then add the salt and cook until the water is gone. Cubed Chicken Potato is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the curd souffle; Add cold milk to the roasted flour and add the remaining boiling milk, stirring constantly. Add butter after removing from heat. Beat egg yolk with sugar. Add curd cheese, cooled bechamel, grated lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla. Add the well-beaten egg whites. Bake the resulting mixture at 200°C for 45 minutes. Curd souffle is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the pasta salad recipe; Boil the pasta in salted boiling water and drain. Then rinse with cold water. When it cools, mix it with half a teaspoon of olive oil. Mix the pickled cucumbers, red peppers and garnish. Add it all to the pasta. Add the yogurt last and mix. Pasta salad is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For grilled bluefish with bay leaves; Wash fish that has been scaled and thoroughly cleaned. Salt both sides and leave for 20 minutes. Place one bay leaf inside the abdomen. Brush olive oil on both sides of the fish. fish; Knee the baking tray after oiling it with oil. Bake the fish in the oven at 200 degrees for 20-25 minutes. For the sauce, whisk finely chopped parsley, half a glass of olive oil, lemon juice and salt. Spoon the sauce over the fish you have placed on the serving plate. Grilled Bluefish is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Mamzana Salad recipe; Roast the eggplants and peppers. While hot, peel the skins and chop 1 cm thick. Finely chop the parsley. Crush the garlic and mix it with the yogurt. Mix the eggplants, peppers, parsley, olive oil, garlic yoghurt and salt in a bowl and transfer to the serving plate. (Optionally, you can pour the garlic yogurt on it without stirring). Mamzana salad is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Pasta with Mushroom Sauce recipe; First, put the mushrooms in water with lemon. After adding the oil, cut the onions into cubes, the peppers into rings and add them to the pot. After frying for 5-10 minutes, chop the tomatoes into cubes and add them to the pot. Add the sauce. Wash the mushrooms and cut them into small pieces and put them in the pot. Add salt and red pepper, cook until mushrooms are soft. Drop the pasta into salted boiling water and cook for 15 minutes. Drain the pasta, put butter in the pan, add the pasta when it melts. Mix and transfer to serving plate. Add the mushroom sauce you prepared on it. Pasta with Mushroom Sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the mushroom saute; First, wash the mushrooms. Fry the onions cut into crescents in half a tea glass of oil. Then chop the garlic into small pieces and add it and continue frying. Chop the peppers in rounds and add them. Then add the mushrooms and cook them until they have evaporated. After the mushrooms have evaporated, peel and dice Add the diced tomatoes and tomato paste. Add salt, black pepper, paprika and thyme and fry for another 4-5 minutes. Mushroom sauteed server is ready. Enjoy your meal :)

For the mushroom turkey saute recipe; Peel the onions and tomatoes, clean the dice and the seeds of the peppers and cut them into thin rings. Heat the oil and add the meat. Saute over high heat, stirring constantly. Add the onion, 1 clove of garlic and peppers and fry for 2 minutes. Add the tomatoes, add salt and pepper and mix. Reduce the heat and cook until the meat is tender. To prepare the sauce, clean and chop the mushrooms. Finely chop the onion and garlic. Melt the butter and fry the onion and garlic. Add mushrooms and saute. Add salt and cream, cook for another 3-4 minutes. Make a puree sauce. Serve hot with sautéed turkey and mushroom sauce. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Mixed Mushroom Salad recipe; First, soak the mushrooms in lemon water. Then fry it in two tablespoons of oil. Finely dice the tomatoes. Finely chop the peppers and olives. After finely chop the parsley, dill, green spring onions, blend all the ingredients. Then prepare a mixture of olive oil and lemon juice and pour it over it. Add the desired amount of salt. Mixed Mushroom Salad is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Mushroom Rice recipe; After sorting the rice, soak it in salty warm water for half an hour. Wash the mushrooms and chop finely. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in the pan, add the mushrooms and fry them. Add salt, pepper and red chili powder. Melt the remaining butter in the pan in which you will cook the pilaf, add the rice that you drained and fry a little. When the rice is roasted, add water and mushrooms and cook on low heat until the water is absorbed. Mushroom rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the buttered ravioli; First, take the flour, make a hole in the middle and add the remaining ingredients, get a dough. Let it rest covered for 20-30 minutes. Add finely chopped onion, parsley, salt and pepper to the minced meat and knead. Divide the dough into 3 parts. Cut 1.5 cm thick strips, then make 1.5 cm wide square pieces from them. Put enough stuffing in each of them and close them in desired shapes. Boil 8 glasses of water in a saucepan, add 2 teaspoons of salt. Drop the ravioli in the water and boil for 10 minutes. Put oil in a separate pan and melt it. Add tomato paste and very little water. On the serving plate, first pour the ravioli, top with yoghurt with garlic, and top with oil with tomato paste. Garnish with mint, sumac and chili peppers. Manti is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Lentil Bulgur Pilaf recipe; First, soak the green lentils and bulgur in a separate bowl in hot water to boil. Melt the oil in the pan in which you will make the pilaf, add the onions into cubes and fry them. Add the garlic to the onions by grating and fry a little. Add the tomato paste and mint and mix. Add the bulgur and lentils and mix a few times. Finally, add your water and cook it on medium heat until it boils, and after boiling, on low heat until the water is absorbed. Bulgur Pilaf with Lentils is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For fruit and nut cake; Pull the hazelnuts into chunks. Chop the dried apricots into cubes. Wash the raisins and soak them in some water. Beat olive oil, sugar and eggs until creamy. When it comes to the consistency of cream, add yoghurt, vanilla and mix. Then sift the flour and baking powder into it with the help of a strainer and mix. Divide the cake batter into 3 equal parts. Add cocoa to one piece, mix, and finally add coarsely ground hazelnuts and mix. 2. Add chopped dried apricots to the cake batter and mix. 3. Add the drained raisins to the cake batter and mix. Put the cake mortar, the dried apricot cake mortar at the bottom of the greased and floured cake mold, the cocoa hazelnut mortar on it, and finally pour the raisin mortar on it. Bake the dried fruit cake in a preheated oven at 185 degrees for 35-40 minutes. Fruit and nut cake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the recipe for Chickpea Karnıyarık; Cook the variegated peeled eggplants on low heat until they soften. After cooking the diced onions with oil, add the grated tomatoes, boiled chickpeas, black pepper, salt and oil on it, mix it together for 5 minutes and leave it on low heat. Stuff the chickpea mixture into the eggplant cut lengthwise in the middle. Add half a tea glass of hot water in the pot and cook for another 10 minutes. Chickpea Karnıyarık dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the chickpea rice soup; Boil the chickpeas that were soaked 8 hours ago. Wash the rice and boil it with 8 glasses of broth. Add the chickpeas and cook. Put the yogurt in a saucepan, add eggs and salt and whisk well. Take two ladles of the boiling soup, add it to the yoghurt, mix it and pour it into the pot. Melt the butter, add the dried mint and drizzle over the soup. Rice soup with chickpeas is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For snapping potatoes; Peel the skin of the potatoes and cut them into rings. Soak them in salted water so that they do not turn brown. Chop the onions and tomatoes into cubes. Fry the ground beef in 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a pan. Add the onions and continue frying. Add the tomatoes and turn for 2 minutes. Salt, pepper and red pepper Add it. Fry the potatoes in oil in a separate pan. Add salt and pepper. Arrange in a round baking dish. Spread the minced meat on it. Add 2 glasses of water. Cook in the oven at 160 degrees. Potato sitting dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the potato pie; Boil the diced potatoes in salted water. After boiling, crush them with a masher. Fry the diced onions with 1 tea glass of vegetable oil. Then add the tomato paste, salt and pepper and continue frying. Lastly, add the boiled and mashed potatoes and mix them. Cut into pieces. Lubricate each piece with oil with the help of a brush. Put 1 tablespoon of the prepared potato mortar on the wide side of the phyllo pieces and roll them around like a spring roll so that they do not open. Mix the milk and egg yolk in a bowl. With the help of a brush, apply on the pastries one by one and add 180 Put in the preheated oven. Potato pie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For stewing meat with potatoes; Chop the meat in cubes. Add enough water and salt to cover it and cook for 45 minutes. When the meat is cooked, add the coarsely chopped potatoes, quartered onion and garlic and boil for another 15 minutes. Stewed Meat with Potatoes is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For cream soup with potatoes; Wash and peel the potatoes, cut them into cubes and boil them. Mash the boiled potatoes by adding a small amount of water. After it becomes puree, add 3 glasses of water, salt and pepper and mix. Melt the butter in a saucepan, add the flour and cook until it changes color. Add warm milk to it and mix well. Put the mashed mixture in the pot. Add 2.5 cups of hot water to it and bring it to a boil over medium heat. Add the cream and cook for 5-6 more minutes on low heat. Creamy Potato Soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For pasta with eggplant sauce; Boil the pasta by adding salt to the boiling water. To prepare the sauce, cut the eggplants into cubes and the peppers in rings. Fry the eggplant, pepper and garlic in a pan with oil. Add the chopped mushrooms to this mixture and fry them. Add the chopped tomatoes and tomato juice for five minutes on low heat. After adding black pepper and salt, mix the pasta with the sauce. Then add grated cheddar on it. Pasta with eggplant sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the eggplant rice recipe with mint; After washing the rice and soaking it in water, drain it well and fry it in 4 tablespoons of oil, stirring, for 10 minutes. Peel the eggplants and cut them into small pieces. Sprinkle salt on it, wait for a while and squeeze out the juice. Mix and fry the chopped onions and then the eggplants in the oil. Add the chopped tomatoes and fry for another 5-10 minutes. Then, add the roasted rice, broth, salt, pepper and sugar to the mixture and cook on low heat. Sprinkle mint on top at the end. Eggplant rice with mint is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For chard wrap; Soak the chard leaves in boiling water for 10 seconds and remove them. Soak the rice in boiling water for 15 minutes. Mix the ground beef, onion, rice, tomato, garlic, 1 tablespoon of tomato paste, salt, pepper and parsley. Clean the stems of the boiled chard leaves. Place 2 teaspoons of the inner mixture in the middle of the leaves and wrap. Mix 1 tablespoon of tomato and 1 tablespoon of pepper paste with 2 glasses of hot water. Add the olive oil and put it on the wrapped wraps. Cook on low heat for 40-45 minutes. Chard Wrap is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the cheese pie; Whisk the oil and yoghurt mixture to soak the phyllo. Place a phyllo dough on the greased tray as a whole and with the edges out. Divide the second phyllo in half and dip it into the mixture and place it in half of the tray. In the same way, dip the other half into the mixture and place it on the rest of the tray. Spread the cheese mortar in between. Divide the third phyllo in half and place it wet on it. Cover the top with the dough hanging from the sides of the tray. Pour all the remaining mixture on the pastry. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees until golden brown. Cheese Pie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the cheese pastry; Pour 3 cups of flour into a deep bowl. Break the yolk of one of the eggs onto the flour. Separate the single egg yolk to brush later on the pastries. Add all the remaining ingredients to the flour and knead. When the dough is ready, divide it into small balls and open the balls in the palm of your hand. In the middle of the opened meringues, place the chili pepper and mint that you mixed with the cheese. Close by pressing the edges. Press firmly so that the two edges stick together. Arrange the pastries on the greased tray. Brush them with egg yolk. Garnish with black cumin and sesame seeds. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees until golden brown. Cheese pastry is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make the leek stuffing, cut the leeks where the green part starts, and cut them all the way through with a knife. Put it in the water you have boiled in the pot and boil it until it softens slightly. After cooling, separate the leeks into layers. Wash and drain the rice and dilute the tomato paste in a bowl. Prepare the stuffing by mixing the minced meat, diluted tomato paste, onion, rice, spices and greens. Arrange the leeks in the shape of an amulet pastry. Arrange the stuffing in the pot, add a tea glass of hot water and cook it on low heat. Stuffed leek is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal!

For the zucchini soup recipe with rice; Fry the diced onion with olive oil. Put the grated zucchini in the pot and fry for a few more minutes. Add hot water to it. After boiling, add the boiled rice. Add the finely chopped dill, salt and pepper and boil for 5 more minutes. Stuffed zucchini with rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Vegetable Soup recipe; Finely chop the onion and fry it with olive oil. Add a tablespoon of flour and mix 1-2 times. Add the leeks, carrots, and celery that have been processed in a food processor. Mix for a few more minutes and add 1.5 liters of boiled water. When the vegetables are lightly cooked, add the potatoes passed through the robot and cook. Then, in a separate bowl, whisk the yolk of an egg with the juice of a lemon. Take the water from the soup little by little with a spoon and warm the seasoning. Then slowly add the seasoning to the cooked soup. Add your salt. Your vegetable soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the vegetable gratin; Wash and clean the zucchini and carrots and chop them coarsely and boil them. Then wash and clean the broccoli, chop coarsely and boil it. After raising the potato, grease the tray with margarine. Spread the boiled and drained vegetables on the tray. Add salt and pepper. Prepare the bechamel sauce. Spread the bechamel sauce on the tray with vegetables. Sprinkle grated cheddar on it and bake. Your vegetable gratin dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the mashed potatoes with vegetables; Peel and boil the potatoes. Mash with a fork and mash. Put the butter in the pan and melt it. Add carrots, corn and peas and fry in oil for 3-4 minutes. Add the mashed potatoes to the pot and mix. Add salt and pepper. Finally, add cream and cheddar cheese, mix and close the bottom of the pot. Vegetable mashed potatoes are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the cheese pie with vegetables; Finely chop the tomatoes, peppers, spring onions and parsley. Crush the cheese. Take the ingredients you have prepared in a bowl, add the egg and mix the ingredients with a spoon. Whisk the milk and melted butter. Spread one of the phyllo dough and spread it with oily milk. Close the other phyllo and repeat the process. Spread the vegetable-cheese mixture on the phyllo and wrap it like a puff pastry. Beat the yogurt and egg yolk to spread it on. Spread the mixture on the pastry and bake in the oven at 170 degrees for 30 minutes. Vegetable Cheese Pie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the juicy meatball recipe; Add the minced meat, grated onion and rice and knead. Put it on a floured plate and roll it all over by dusting it with flour. Put the margarine and tomato paste in a pan and fry the tomato paste. Add the peeled and diced potatoes and carrots on it. Add water after 1-2 minutes of frying. When it starts to boil, add the meatballs and spices. Cook for 120-25 minutes on medium heat. Sprinkle finely chopped parsley on top. Juicy meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Chicken Pasta recipe; Put the pasta in boiling salted water and cook for 10 minutes. While the pasta is cooking, fry the diced onion and diced peppers in a tablespoon of oil. Add the peeled and diced tomatoes and tomato paste and cook until the tomatoes are melted. When the tomatoes start to melt, shred the chicken breast and add it to the tomato mixture. Add the garlic and seasonings. Then drain the pasta and add it to the sauce. Cook the pasta with the sauce for another minute. Lastly, add the chopped parsley. Chicken Pasta is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Ali Nazik with Pepper Paste; Finely chop the tomatoes, peppers and onions. Take the butter in the pan and melt it. Fry the minced meat and the finely chopped ingredients on medium heat until they release their juices. Crush the garlic with a little salt. Finely chop the roasted eggplants on the cutting board. Fry the tomato paste and butter for 2-3 minutes and remove from the stove. Mix the garlic, eggplant and yoghurt and transfer to the serving plate. Spread the meat mixture you prepared on it and serve it by pouring the tomato paste sauce on it. Ali, your kind meal is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Albanian liver recipe; peel the potatoes and rinse the liver with water. Chop the potatoes and liver into cubes. Meanwhile, put the oil in the frying pan to heat up. First put the potatoes and fry them. Then flour half of the liver and throw it into the hot oil. After mixing 2-3 times, when the livers are browned, remove them from the oil and put them on a napkin lined plate. All the livers and potatoes After frying all the potatoes and livers, put them all in a deep bowl and mix them. After mixing, spread it again on the serving plate. Spread the sumac and finely chopped parsley on it. Albanian liver dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the quince dessert; peel the quinces and cut them in half horizontally. Set the seeds aside. Arrange the quinces in the pot with the middle part facing up. Add water so that it reaches half of the quinces. Add 4 cloves, cinnamon sticks, quince seeds and sugar to the pot and cook on low heat for about 1 hour until the quinces are soft. After cooling, serve with the addition of walnuts and cream. Enjoy your meal :)

For the hazelnut pumpkin dessert; Clean the inside and shells of the pumpkin and cut it into two finger widths. Arrange it in a single row in a flat pan. Sprinkle granulated sugar on it. Leave it for 1-2 hours and add half a tea glass of water. Then cook it on low heat for about 40 minutes. It will absorb the remaining water while resting. Add crushed hazelnuts while serving. Pumpkin dessert is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Biscuit Cake recipe; Cook by mixing all the custard ingredients except vanilla so that there are no lumps. After it boils, take it off the heat and add the vanilla and whisk. Lightly moisten the bottom of a medium-sized pyrex with a little milk and place a layer of biscuits on it. Pour a third of the custard over it. Do this in the same way with 3 layers of biscuits and 3 layers of pudding. Then let it cool in the fridge. After cooling, garnish with nutmeg. Biscuit Cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the meatballs with broccoli; Cut the broccoli into florets. Sprinkle salt on it and steam it. Remove the seeds from the red peppers, boil them in water for 10 minutes and drain. While it's hot, put it in a blender. Add olive oil, lemon juice and salt on it and pull again. Add paprika and set the sauce aside. To prepare the meatballs, put the ground meat in a bowl. Add grated onion, soaked and squeezed bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper and water and knead. Cut walnut-sized pieces from the mortar you prepared and prepare round meatballs. Cook front to back in oil. Transfer the broccoli and meatballs to the serving plate. Serve with sauce on top. Enjoy your meal :)

For the steamed kebab; Chop the meat to the size of shallots and stew. Peel the onion and garlic and add to the meat as a whole. Wash and grate the tomatoes. Add bay leaves, salt, pepper, thyme and tomato grated and close the lid of the casserole. Cook on low heat for about 2 hours. Before serving. Take the bay leaves from inside and sprinkle with dill. Your steamed kebab is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Büryan Pilaf recipe; Soak the rice in warm, salty and lemon water for half an hour. Fry the meat in a saucepan until it releases its water. Add 2 fingers of hot water and 1 pinch of salt and boil until the meat is tender. Clean the onion and cut it into piyaz. Clean and grate the carrot. Wash and drain the rice with plenty of water. Heat the oil in the pan and fry the rice. Spread the meat in a flat pan. Place the diced onions and grated carrots on it. Spread the rice over the vegetables and add the hot broth, grated tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook the rice until the water evaporates. After infusing for 15-20 minutes, invert the pot onto the serving plate. Büryan Pilaf is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Circassian chicken; Boil the chicken with 4 glasses of water by adding parsley, bay leaf, onion, salt, and black pepper. Strain and smash. Roast the walnuts, red pepper, bread and garlic. Gradually add the chicken broth. Mix half of the mixture with the chicken meat. Remove to serving plate. Pour the remaining sauce over it and let it rest in the refrigerator for at least a few hours. Finally, burn the ground pepper in the butter and pour it over it. Your Circassian chicken dish is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the eggplant salad recipe with tomatoes; Roast the eggplants in the oven. Peel the skins of the roasted eggplants. Chop into small pieces. In a deep bowl, mix the eggplant, lemon juice, olive oil and salt well. Put the mixture in a salad bowl. Finely chop the onion. Sprinkle the onions over the eggplants. Peel and dice the tomatoes. Salt and sprinkle over the onions. Drizzle olive oil over the top of the salad. Eggplant salad with tomatoes is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the wedding soup; Chop 250 g of beef into dice. Take it in a pan and fry it without oil until the water is absorbed with the onion. Add 8 glasses of water and cook until the meat is tender. Whisk 1 egg, 2 tablespoons of flour and the juice of half a lemon in a bowl. Add 2 tablespoons of the boiling water to the mixture and whisk again. Add the mixture little by little into the pot and bring it to a boil. Divide into serving bowls and garnish with 15 g butter roasted mint and paprika. Your wedding soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the oven meatball recipe; finely chop the onions. Grate 3 tomatoes and chop 1 tomato into rings. Crush the garlic. Peel and chop the potatoes. Soak and squeeze 2 slices of stale bread. Put the minced meat, squeezed stale bread, onion, garlic, black pepper, cumin and salt in a bowl and knead. Form the kneaded meatballs into balls. Prepare the meatballs by flattening walnut-sized pieces of meatball mortar in the palm of your hand. Fry the potatoes first and then the meatballs with 4 tablespoons of olive oil. Prepare the sauce by mixing tomato paste, salt, 1 glass of boiling water in the bowl. Arrange the meatballs and potatoes in the tray. Add grated tomatoes on it. Then pour the sauce and 2 tablespoons of olive oil on the meatballs. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 30 minutes. Oven meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal .

For the Baked Pasta recipe, boil the pasta with water for 15-20 minutes and strain it before starting the preparation. Immediately add 1 tablespoon of oil and mix it so that it does not stick. In a separate bowl, mix the flour, oil and milk. Mix the pasta into this mortar. Grease a square tray with margarine, sprinkle a little flour and pour the pasta dough into the tray. Sprinkle the white cheese all over it. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown. Baked Cheese Pasta is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal .

For the spinach meatball recipe; After washing the spinach and juicing it well, add the finely chopped green onions, egg, breadcrumbs and seasonings and start mixing it with the spinach in a bowl. Knead until it reaches the consistency that can be shaped, form two finger-thick meatballs and arrange them on a plate. Let the meatballs you shaped rest in the refrigerator for a while. Place the meatballs you have rested in the refrigerator on the baking tray and bake in a preheated oven at 180 degrees for 35-40 minutes. Serve the meatballs with yogurt if you wish. Spinach patties are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For fava; Soak the broad beans overnight. The next day, drain the water, wash it and put it in the pot. Chop the onion and add it to the broad beans. Add salt and sugar. Cook it by adding water to it. Cook the broad beans until they absorb their water and become crushed. Pass them through a blender and make them smooth. Wet the deep glass bowl with water. Pour the prepared fava into it. Let it rest in the refrigerator for a few hours. Remove the fava from the mold by turning it upside down. Pour the sauce you prepared by mixing lemon juice and olive oil on it. Garnish with the chopped dill last. Fava is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the rose pastry; Cook the minced meat with very little oil until it absorbs the water it leaves. Mix the minced meat with the parsley and spices. Lay the yufka on top of each other and divide it into two equal parts. Brush the top one with a yoghurt mortar. Spread a tablespoon of minced meat from the inside and form a roll. Apply mortar with yoghurt on the roll and wrap it in the shape of a rose. Brush them with egg yolk and bake in the oven at 200 C. Blueberry is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the anchovy pilaf recipe; For pilaf, add the oil to the pan, finely chop the onion and fry it. Wash and soak the rice in hot water for half an hour, strain it and add it to the pot. Add sugar, salt, all the spices and currants and add the water, cook on low heat until the water is absorbed. Roast the pine nuts in a separate pan without oil. When the rice is cooked, add the roasted peanuts and finely chopped dill. Let the rice rest for 15 minutes. Grease the bottom and sides of individual casserole dishes. Arrange the anchovies first on the bottom and then vertically to the sides so that their shiny surface is in the casserole dish. According to the size of the casserole, put a few spoons of rice and close the anchovies overflowing from the sides. Put a little butter on them and bake at 200 degrees for about 20 minutes. Anchovy pilaf is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

After washing the carrots, scrape the skins and grate them. In another bowl, mix the eggs, flour and salt to form a dough. Add grated carrots to this mixture and mix well. Heat the oil in a pan. Take a spoonful of the prepared mixture and fry it in hot oil on top and bottom. Serve with yogurt on top.

For the recipe for pasta with carrot sauce; Put 2 tablespoons of oil, 1 teaspoon of salt and water in a saucepan and let it boil. When the water boils, cook the pasta in boiling water. On the other side, put 4 tablespoons of oil in a pan and grate the carrot on it. Add the remaining salt and cook on low heat for about 5 minutes. Turn off the heat and wait for the mixture to warm up, add the yogurt and mix. Take the pasta on a serving plate and pour the sauce over it and serve. Pasta with carrot sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For hummus; sort the chickpeas and soak them overnight. Boil it well, remove the skins and beat them in a mortar. Take it in a bowl and add the tahini, crushed garlic, red pepper and salt. Add olive oil and lemon juice little by little. Place on a plate and garnish with lemon slices, olives and parsley leaves. Hummus is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For Hünkar liked; Wrap the eggplants in aluminum foil and roast them on the stove. Peel and mash after roasting. Fry the flour and butter. Add the milk little by little and add the salt. Mix the sauce with the crushed eggplants. Take the whole mixture in a deep plate. Put the meat in the pan and cook it with a little oil until the water has evaporated. Add the flour. Add the garlic and tomato paste, then add salt and pepper. Put the meat on the serving plate. When serving, put your favorite on the plate first. Then place the meat in the middle of the skewer. Hünkar liked it is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Izmir meatball recipe; Pull the other ingredients except the minced meat in the robot. Add the minced meat and knead by hand, prepare the meatballs and make large rounds. Fry in a teflon pan with little oil. In a separate pot, cook the tomato sauce. Put the potato slices you cut thickly in a baking dish and the meatballs on it. Grate the raw potato, mix it with a little salt and fry it in a pan with very little oil for 2 minutes until the potatoes are soft. Put a pinch of potato grater on the meatballs. Drizzle a spoonful of tomato sauce over each and pour the remaining sauce into the baking dish. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees until the potatoes are soft. Izmir meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For zucchini kalye with olive oil; dice the onion, add the oil to the pan and fry the onion. Add the tomato paste on the onions before they are completely fried. Finely chop the green peppers and add them to the pot. Scrape the outside of the carrots and zucchini. Chop into cubes. Peel the skins of the tomatoes and add the edible chops. Add salt and red pepper too. Add half a glass of hot water to it and cook on low heat for 20 minutes. Pumpkin kalye with olive oil is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Pumpkin Meatballs recipe; Clean and grate the zucchini. Leave it in the strainer for 10 minutes. Squeeze the water thoroughly. Clean and chop the parsley and dill. Clean and chop the spring onions. Crush the feta cheese. Take eggs, baking powder, flour, feta cheese and olive oil in a bowl and mix. Add zucchini, dill, parsley, spring onion, salt and pepper and mix. Pour the mixture onto a greased baking tray and spread. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 10 minutes. Sprinkle the cheddar cheese on top and cook the zucchini meatballs for another 10 minutes. Pumpkin patties are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

To make women's bud meatballs; Mix water and salt in a saucepan. When it boils, add the rice and boil for 10 minutes. Take the softened rice with a strainer and leave it aside to let the juices drain. Chop the onion finely. Fry half of the minced meat with the onion in 2 tablespoons of oil and set aside to cool. Put the roasted ground beef, raw ground beef, boiled rice in the kneading bowl and break an egg on them. Add the black pepper, cumin and salt and knead well. Put in the refrigerator for 1 hour. Take egg-sized pieces from the meatballs, roll them and flatten them with your hands. Place the meatballs you prepared on a tray, and put the flour next to the tray. Crack the eggs into a deep bowl, add a little salt and whisk well. Put the oil in a deep pan and heat it. Dip the meatballs first in flour and then in egg and fry them in oil. Kadinbudu meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Keshkul recipe; Put the milk, sugar and vanilla in a saucepan and cook. Whisk the egg yolk and wheat starch in half a bowl of water until they dissolve. When the milk starts to boil, slowly add the mixture to the pot. Cook, stirring, until it thickens. Transfer to serving bowls and leave to cool in the refrigerator. Keşkul is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the minced peas; Dice the onions and fry them in olive oil. Add the minced meat and continue frying. After the ground beef is roasted, add salt and add the diced potatoes and peas and fry them. For a glass of hot water, melt 3 spoons of pepper paste and pour it on top. Add enough hot water to rise above the ingredients in the pot and cook. Minced Peas are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the creme caramel; Boil 3 tablespoons of sugar with a cup of water and make molasses-colored caramel and pour it into the mold. Heat the mold slightly and cover all sides. Beat the eggs with a wire. Add vanilla, sugar and milk. Stir the sugar until it melts. Pour the sweetened milk into the caramel mold and place it in a large saucepan. Put hot water in the pan half way past the rim. Cook on the fire without boiling the water and without hardening the cream. After it cools down, press the edges and turn it into a plate. Creme caramel is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the crepe cake recipe; First of all, for the cream, put the milk in a saucepan and add the flour, starch and sugar to it and mix it on the stove and bring it to a boil. Take the boiling mixture off the stove and let it cool. For the pancakes, beat the eggs and sugar with a mixer. Add wheat flour, cocoa powder, oil, and get a softer dough than cake batter. Heat the pancake pan, take half a scoop of dough, put it in the middle of the pan, distribute it with the help of the ladle and cook. Put the cooked pancakes in a container with a lid. On the other hand, put labneh cheese, whipped cream and vanilla into the warm cream and beat with the help of a mixer. Spread the cream between the crepes and roll them up. Place the wrapped pancakes in a covered container and leave them in the refrigerator for a couple of hours. Before serving, streak the tahini on the cake. Crepe cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the dry bean (meat) recipe; Put enough hot water to pass 4-5 fingers over the dry beans that you have soaked in water overnight and boil on the stove at a high temperature. Then cook the beans in their own water on low heat until they are soft. While the beans are cooking, chop and put 4 onions as edible in a separate large pot. Add the olive oil and fry the onions. Finely chop the meat, wash it, add it to the pot and fry them too. Continue frying until the meat absorbs the water they have left. Then chop the tomato paste and hot peppers into small pieces and add them to the pot. Add boiling water to the pot until it reaches the top of the meat. Cook until the meat is tender. When the dry beans are cooked, add the beans to the pot with the meat and mix well. Finally, sprinkle salt and continue boiling. After a few minutes of boiling, turn off the heat. Dry beans (with meat) are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the dry bean (without meat) recipe; Put it in the pot so that it covers the dried beans you have soaked in water before and boil it. Chop the onions. Put the onions and sunflower oil in another pot and fry the onions. After frying, add the tomato paste and continue frying. Add salt and pepper and mix a few more times. Add the boiled beans to the pot and add 6 cups of hot water and continue to boil. Turn off the heat when the beans are fully cooked. Dry beans (without meat) are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the lokma dessert; Put the flour, salt, sugar in the mixing bowl and mix well, make the middle like a pool and get a soft dough by putting the yeast, milk, melted butter, egg and some water in the pool. Boil water and 4 glasses of sugar. Finally, drip lemon. Throw the dough you prepared into sherbet, let it sit for 10 minutes, sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg on it and serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the lentil patties; Wash 1 glass of red lentils and put them on fire with 1 liter of water. Boil the lentils until they are mashed and slightly watery. Take 2 cups of fine bulgur in a flat bowl, add the lentils and mix. Cover the bowl with aluminum foil and wait until the lentils swell. In the meantime, chop 2 onions for cooking and fry the onions in a saucepan with a tea glass of olive oil. Add 1.5 tablespoons of pepper paste and 1.5 tablespoons of tomato paste and continue frying. Add 1 teaspoon of black pepper and paprika and mix. Finally, add 1 tea glass of hot water to the pot and boil for 2 minutes. Add this mixture to the bulgur and lentil mixture and mix well. Wash and chop 5-6 stalks of green onions. Wash and finely chop a bunch of parsley in the same way. Add the parsley, green onions and 1.5 teaspoons of salt and knead for 10-15 minutes. Take walnut-sized pieces of the mortar and shape them in the palm of your hand. Place the lettuce leaves on the serving plate and arrange the meatballs you prepared on the lettuce leaves. Lentil Meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

To make cornmeal cookies; Separate the yolks of 2 eggs. Mix margarine, oil, sugar and water. Add in the cornmeal and baking powder and mix. Add white flour and knead a dough that does not stick to the hand. Pieces of dough are cut off, shaped, dipped in egg white and placed on a tray with greaseproof paper. Baked in a preheated 180-degree oven until golden brown. Your cornmeal cookie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the banana cake; Grease the cake mold with a little margarine, sprinkle some flour on it. In a bowl, beat the eggs well with the vanilla and sugar until they turn white. Add the flour, salt and baking powder to it. Keep mixing with the mixer. Add all the remaining ingredients, except bananas, into the cake batter and beat with a mixer. Mash the bananas with a fork and mash them and add them to the cake batter together with the walnuts. Mix them in the dough until the bananas are evenly spread all over. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for about 1 hour. Banana cake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Chickpea Meal (Meat) recipe; The night before, wash the chickpeas, put them in a pot and add enough water to cover them by 3 fingers. The next day, add some water to the chickpeas and boil until soft. Chop the onions and fry them in olive oil in a pan. Add the meat, cook some meat, add the tomato paste and fry for another 2-3 minutes. Then pour boiling water over the meat and boil it until the meat is tender. When the meat is tender, add the chickpeas. Cook for another 5 minutes and add salt. Meaty chickpeas is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the chickpea dish (without meat); Put the vegetable oil and the peppers you have cut into small pieces in the pot, fry for 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly. Grate the tomatoes and add them to the pot and fry for a minute or two. After frying, add the tomato paste and mix. Lastly, add the chickpeas, salt, pepper and sugar and fry a little more. Add boiling water and let it cook for 20-25 minutes. Chickpea dish (without meat) is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the mashed potatoes; Peel the potatoes and cut them into large cubes. Put the diced potatoes in the pot. Add enough milk to cover them slightly. Add the salt and butter pieces to the milk. Let the potatoes soften well by mixing them so that they do not stick to the bottom. When the potatoes are soft, turn off the stove and pass it through the blender. Mashed Potatoes are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the egg with potatoes; peel and chop the potatoes. Then chop the potato slices lengthwise again and get cubes. Put the oil in the pan and heat the pan. Put the potatoes in a heated pan, add salt and fry. Meanwhile, whisk the eggs in another bowl. When the potatoes are browned, pour the egg over the potatoes. Close the lid of the pan and cook the egg. Eggs with potatoes are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make chard roast; Put the olive oil in the pan and when the oil is hot, put the onion and garlic that you have chopped for cooking. Then add the tomato paste and the tomatoes you cut into cubes and fry them. After adding the finely chopped chard, add hot water and bulgur, mix and close the lid. Cook on very low heat. Chard roast is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the potato soup; first peel and dice the onions and potatoes. Fry the onions in a saucepan with 2 tablespoons of margarine. Add the hot broth to the pot. When the broth boils, add the potatoes and continue boiling. Pass it through the last colander and put it on the stove and add milk in it. After boiling for 10 minutes, add salt and mix. Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine in a pan, add oil and fry the red pepper. Divide the soup you prepared into bowls and pour some of the oily sauce you prepared on it. Potato soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the potato patties; Grate the potatoes finely and squeeze out the excess water by squeezing them with your hand and put them in a bowl. Boil the potatoes and grate them. Add flour, black pepper, salt, egg, dill and cheddar cheese and mix. Cut off small pieces from the mixture you prepared and roll them in the form of meatballs. Beat the egg yolk and find the meatballs. Heat the oil in the pan and fry the meatballs you prepared. Potato patties are now ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

To make cheesecake; Put 3 eggs and 1 glass of yogurt in a deep bowl and mix at the highest speed of the mixer. Continuing to mix, add 1/4 glass of oil, 300 g of curd cheese, half a tablespoon of paprika, 1 tablespoon of thyme, half a teaspoon of black pepper and flour. Add chopped parsley and dill and mix 1-2 times. Add the baking powder last and mix several times at the lowest speed of the mixer. Grease the cake mold and pour the cake into the mold. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 40 minutes. Cheesecake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For Emek dessert with pudding; Arrange the meat on the tray. Boil the sugar with 1.5 cups of water. Pour the sugar over the meat and let it cool. Prepare the pudding according to the recipe on the package. Add cinnamon close to taking it from the stove and mix. Pour the pudding on the meat and flatten it. Decorate with coconut. After cooling for 2 hours Serve sliced. Enjoy your meal :)

For the quince dessert with pudding; Peel and cut the quinces in half and remove the cored parts with a spoon. Put water, granulated sugar, cloves and quince seeds in the pot. After 10 minutes, add the grated apple on it. Cook the quinces until they are soft. Then place them on a baking tray and fill the grated apples in the middle. Bake in a preheated 150 degree oven for 10 minutes. On the other hand, prepare the pudding with three glasses of milk. After it is cooled, pour it on the serving plate. Place the quinces on it. Whisk the whipped cream with 1 glass of milk and fill it into the squeezer. Serve with whipped cream on the quinces. Enjoy your meal :)

To make puff pastry; open the middle of the flour. Put eggs, yogurt and sunflower oil in it. Add the baking soda and water and knead the mixture into a dough. Cover with a cloth and rest for 15 minutes. Crumble the cheese for the inside. Finely chop the parsley and add to the cheese. Divide the rested dough into six equal parts. Roll out these pieces to the size of a plate. Put them on top of each other, three at a time, lubricating them. Thinly roll out one of the three pieces with a rolling pin. Put the cheese inside you prepared on half of the phyllo. Cover the remaining half of the phyllo on the cheese mortar. Press the edges. Cut triangular pieces. Press the open parts of the triangles again. Prepare the other three parts in the same way. Fry in oil until both sides are cooked. Puff pastry is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make Revani; Beat eggs and sugar. Add the other ingredients, mix and get a cake-like dough. Spread the mixture on a greased round baking tray and cook at 175C. Boil water and sugar for the syrup. Add 2 drops of lemon juice before removing from the stove. After removing the tray from the oven, pour 1 glass of cold water over it. Pour the warm syrup over the raisin. Garnish with nutmeg last. Revani is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make meatballs; Knead all the ingredients except the garnish and make a meatball dough. Continue kneading for 3-5 minutes and lightly oil the baking dish and spread the ground beef in it. Add a little salt to the garnish mixture and spread it in the middle of the minced meat. Roll the ground meat so that the meatballs are joined at the bottom. Brush egg white on it. Put 5 teaspoons of butter on it and bake in the oven at 200 C for 40 minutes. Meatloaf is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the American Salad; Boil the diced potatoes and carrots. Then cut the pickled gherkins into small cubes. Put all the chopped ingredients in a large bowl. Mix the yogurt and mayonnaise. Finally, mix the mayonnaise mixture with all the other ingredients. American salad is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

To make sheet roasting; heat the hair on the stove. Add the oil and add the meat. Fry the meat for 15 minutes until the water is gone. Then throw in the diced onions and fry for another 5 minutes on medium heat. After frying the chopped peppers for 2-3 minutes, add the chopped tomatoes and cook. Add salt and pepper last. Sheet roasting is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make plain cake; Beat eggs and sugar. Add milk and oil and mix. Finally, add flour, baking powder and vanilla and mix them all together. Pour into a greased tray. Bake for 30 minutes in the oven set at 170 degrees. Plain cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the vegetable red lentil soup recipe; sort and wash the red lentils and rice. Put it in a pot with plenty of water. Grate the onion, carrot and potato. Chop the tomatoes and peppers into cubes. Add it to the pot along with the bay leaf. Cook on low heat for 30 minutes. After adding the oil, boil for 10 more minutes, take the bay leaf out and add the spices. Red lentil soup with vegetables is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Vegetable Rice recipe; Clean the rice and add enough hot water to cover it, add 1 tablespoon of salt, mix and wait. Put 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a pan, fry the garlic, salt and rice for 5 minutes. Add the carrots and fry for 2-3 minutes, add the zucchini and fry a little more. Finally, add the peas and cook for a few more minutes. Put the remaining oil in a flat pan and fry the vermicelli until they turn brown. Add the rice water to it and fry it a little more. Then add water to it and cook until the water is absorbed. When the rice absorbs its water, add the roasted vegetables that you prepared in the pan to the rice and mix. Add the pepper and salt and mix. Cook for a few more minutes and turn off the heat and let it rest. Vegetable Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the noodle soup recipe; Finely dice 3 tomatoes. Put the tomatoes in the pot and cook with 1.5 tablespoons of butter until the tomatoes are mashed. Then add 1 liter of boiled water and add the noodle to the pot. Add salt when the noodles are cooked. Noodle soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Noodle Rice recipe; Wash the rice and soak it in hot water for half an hour. Then put the butter in a flat pan and add the barley noodles and fry them. Drain the rice and add it to the pot and continue to fry. Add the water that comes out when you drain the rice, add the salt to the rice, and then cook it on medium heat until it absorbs its water. Vermicelli Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe of Şekerpare; First, bring the water and sugar to the boil and prepare the syrup. Add lemon juice to the boiling syrup and boil for 1-2 more minutes and let it cool. For the dough of Şekerparen; Mix the softened margarine, eggs, powdered sugar and semolina. Add the wheat flour, baking powder and vanilla and knead to obtain a dough with the consistency of an earlobe. Arrange on the greased tray by giving it an oval shape. Finally, apply egg yolk on it and scratch the top with the help of a fork. Bake at 180 degrees until it is browned. Pour the cold sherbet you prepared on the dessert that comes out of the oven. Şekerpare is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For purslane; Wash and chop the purslane thoroughly. Add olive oil, diced onions to the pan and fry the onion. Add the grated tomatoes and the garlic that you cut in half to the pot and cook the tomato. When the tomatoes are cooked, add half of the purslane to the pot, put the rice on top, then put the other half of the purslane on top. After boiling, cook on low heat for 20 minutes. Your purslane dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For spaghetti bolognese; Fry the ground beef with olive oil and butter. Add the flour and add the tomato paste when it is slightly browned. Peel the skin of the tomatoes, chop them and add to the minced meat. Put salt, sugar, basil, spices and garlic. Add the broth and cook. Boil the spaghetti in salted boiling water and drain. Transfer it to a serving plate and pour the sauce over it. Spaghetti bolognese is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the water pastry; Mix eggs, milk, oil and water thoroughly in a deep bowl. Lay a phyllo dough on the greased baking tray. Tear off the overflowing edges. Wrap another phyllo into a roll, tear it off, dip it into the milky mixture you have prepared and place it side by side on the tray. Repeat the same process with another phyllo. Release your stuff. Tear off the other 2 phyllo pieces again, dip them in the milk mixture and place them on the stuffing consisting of cheese and parsley. Cover the remaining phyllo on the top and pour the remaining milk mixture over the pastry. Bake in a preheated 190 C oven until golden brown. The water pastry is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

To make water pudding; Put the milk and water in a saucepan. Mix granulated sugar, starch and flour in a bowl. Add to the milky milk. Cook, stirring constantly. Put it in my wetted debt. Leave it in the refrigerator overnight. Sprinkle rose water and powdered sugar on it and serve. Enjoy your meal :)

For the rice pudding recipe; Wash the rice and put it in a pot with 1 liter of water and cook it. Then add cold milk to it. While waiting for it to boil, crush 2 tablespoons of rice flour in a bowl with 1 glass of cold water. Take 1-2 ladles of the milk that is boiling in the pot, add it to the bowl and mix. Then add this mixture in the bowl to the pot and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add 2.5 cups of granulated sugar to the milk that is being cooked, mix and continue to boil. Divide the rice pudding into bowls and leave to cool in the refrigerator. Garnish with cinnamon when serving. Rice pudding is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the milk semolina dessert; Put milk, semolina and sugar in a deep saucepan and mix. After it thickens and starts to boil, sprinkle the vanilla and mix. Pour it into the molds you have moistened with water. After cooling, take it out by turning it upside down in the container you will serve. Milk semolina dessert is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)

To make sawdust pastry; For the stuffing of the pastry, add the meat to the vegetable oil and fry it. Put the cubed onion on the meat and continue to fry. Add the peas, salt and pepper on it. Mix it and put the finely chopped parsley on it. Sprinkle salt on the flour in the dough mixing bowl, after mixing, open the middle like a pool. Put vinegar, water and oil on it and mix. Knead the dough until it has a consistency and roll it out. Spread the melted margarine on it and roll it. Leave it to rest in the refrigerator for half an hour. Cut pieces from the dough you have rested and roll it into squares with the help of a rolling pin. Put the inside that you have prepared in the middle of the dough, which you have opened squarely, and close it in the form of an envelope. After laying it on the tray, brush it with egg yolk and bake at 190 degrees. Chip pie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Tarhana soup recipe; First, fry the green pepper, grated tomato, garlic and tomato paste in oil. After roasting, put water on it and let it boil. Open the tarhana well in a bowl with water. Take some of the boiling water in the pot and put it in the tarhana. Then pour it into the pot. Add salt and spices, stirring constantly. Tarhana soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

To make chicken patties; Wash and drain the chicken meat. Bring the meat to the consistency of minced meat by pulling the meat on the blade part of the robot. Add salt and pepper to the meat. Then add the green onions, garlic, bread crumbs, dill and egg yolk. Mix all the ingredients in the robot. Wet your hands with egg white and then prepare the chicken patties. Dip the meatballs first in egg white and then in breadcrumbs and fry. Chicken patties are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For Chicken Saute; Cut the chicken into small cubes, sauté in a pan with 2 teaspoons of olive oil for 5 minutes. Then put the chickens on a plate. Add 2 teaspoons of olive oil to the same pan and start sautéing the finely chopped peppers. After the peppers are softened, add the pepper paste to the pan and continue to fry by stirring. Finely chop the garlic, add and mix. After mixing, add the chicken to the pan. After mixing the ingredients well, add the tomatoes you cut into cubes. After the tomatoes soften, add the spices and mix. Then add the hot water to the pan and mix. After the water is absorbed, close the bottom of the chicken sauté. Chicken Saute is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For roasting green beans; finely chop the onions. After cleaning the heads and awns of the beans, cut them in half. Clean and grate the skins of the tomatoes. Add the vegetable oil, onion, chopped beans and grated tomato to the pot. Stir fry for 20 minutes on low heat. Then add 4 cups of hot water and salt. After the beans cook for 20 minutes on low heat, break the eggs on them and close the lid and continue cooking until the eggs are cooked. After the eggs are cooked, mix them a few times and serve. Roasted green beans are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the tiramisu recipe; To prepare the cream, put milk, flour, eggs and 2 tablespoons of granulated sugar in a saucepan and pass it through a blender. Put it on the fire, mix it constantly, cook it until it gets the consistency of custard and cool it for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, mix two tablespoons of instant coffee and granulated sugar with hot water. Wet the insides of the sponge cakes you cut in half with this. When the cream has cooled, add a packet of labneh cheese and mix. Spread half of the cream thickly on the sponge cake on the serving plate and cover the sponge cake layer. Cover the sponge cakes completely with the remaining cream. Then sprinkle cocoa and Turkish coffee. Tiramisu is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

To make flour soup; Put the butter in the pan and melt it. Then put the flour and fry it. Stir and fry continuously for 10 minutes. Add water on it. After boiling, burn the mint and red pepper in a spoonful of oil and pour into the soup. Flour Soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the green lentil soup; Dice the onion and fry it in oil. After adding the tomato paste, wash and drain the lentils and add them. Peel the potatoes and carrots, cut them into small pieces, put them in the pot, add water and salt and let them cook. When the lentils are cooked, run the soup through the blender. In a separate pan, burn the red pepper in butter and pour into the soup. Green lentil soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For the Green Rice recipe; After finely chop the parsley, dill and mint, put half of them in boiling salted water. Then put the butter in a flat pan and add the rice that has been soaked in water beforehand. After frying the rice a little, add the pepper and salt. Add 3 cups of water and cook until the water is absorbed. After the rice absorbs the water, add the greens and mix. Cook for a few more minutes with the lid closed, then turn off the heat and let it rest. Green Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the sherbet of the yogurt dessert; Boil 4 cups of sugar, water and lemon. When the syrup is made, take out the lemon and cool the syrup. Put the eggs in a mixing bowl and beat them together with the sugar until they turn white. Add the yogurt and margarine and mix. Add flour, semolina, baking powder and vanilla and mix well on low speed. Pour the dough into a greased and lightly sprinkled mold. Bake in a preheated 200 C oven. Take it out of the oven and pour the syrup over it. Garnish with nutmeg after making the syrup. Yogurt dessert is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

For fried carrots with yogurt; scrape off the tops of the carrots and chop into rings. Cook in boiling water until soft. After draining the water, let it cool. Put flour on a plate, thicken with water and dip the carrots one by one into this mixture. Put oil in a pan. Fry the carrots by throwing them in the pan. Take it on a serving plate and serve with slightly diluted yoghurt next to it. Enjoy your meal :)

For frying cauliflower with yoghurt, first separate the cauliflower flower by flower. Take it in a pot and boil it by adding enough water to reach half of it. Drain the boiled cauliflower. Make a sauce by whisking the milk, salt and egg in a separate bowl. Put the cauliflower in this sauce and fry it in hot oil. Beat 3 cloves of garlic and mix it into the yogurt. Take the cauliflower on a serving plate and pour the garlic yoghurt over it. Your fried cauliflower is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal :)

To make chicken yoghurt salad, boil the chicken and dice it after it cools. Peel the carrot, cut it into cubes and boil it.
