Before turning off the bottom, mix it a couple of times, close the lid and the bottom and let it rest. Whole Wheat Bulgur Pilaf with Tomatoes is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe of bulgur pilaf with chickpeas; Put the butter and oil in the pan and light the bottom. After the butter has melted, strain the chickpeas and put them in the pot and fry them a little. After the chickpeas are roasted, add the washed bulgur to the pot and fry the bulgur for a while. Dissolve the bouillon in 2 cups of boiling water and add it to the pot. It is cooked on low heat until the water is absorbed. Bulgur Pilaf with Chickpea is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

To prepare oven-baked pasta with olives; Put salted water and a few drops of olive oil in the pot and boil the pasta. While waiting for the water to boil, wash and extract the dill. Finely chop after removing. Beat the garlic in a mortar with salt. Take out the pits of the green olives one by one. After removing it, put it in a pan. Cook for 2-3 minutes on low heat. Open the lid and add the dill and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon. At this time, the pasta, which is cooked to a consistency that will not stick to the teeth, is filtered out of the water. Pour it over the olives with dill in the pan and mix. Pour four tablespoons of olive oil on top and dip all the pasta in olive oil. Lightly grease an ovenproof dish. Pour the breadcrumbs into it and find the inside of the bowl. Pour the pasta into the crumbled baking dish. Spread the grated cheddar cheese on top. After heating the oven to 200 ° C, put the container in the oven. Bake for 10 minutes until browned. Olive Oven Pasta is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Mushroom Bulgur Pilaf recipe; Fry the mushrooms and finely chopped peppers in 2 tablespoons of oil in a rice cooker until they release their water and evaporate. Then add the butter and when the oil melts, add the tomato paste to the mixture and mix. When the smell of tomato paste comes out, add the other ingredients and continue frying. Then, filter the findings that were previously kept in hot water, add and mix. Add water, salt, and spices to the bulgur that you have thoroughly mixed with the ingredients and let it cook until the water is gone by closing the lid. When it is covered with eye and water, close the bottom and let it rest for 15 minutes. Enjoy your meal

For the recipe of Istanbul Pilaf; Extract 2 cups of rice. Soak in hot salt water for an hour. Wash and drain the water. Roast 100 grams of almonds in 2 tablespoons of butter. Then add 1 teaspoon of saffron on it and mix it. Drain the rice and add it to the almonds. Add salt, 2 cubes of sugar, pre-boiled and finely chopped chicken breast, 1 tea glass of peas and 3 glasses of water on it. Cook for 15 minutes on low heat. Add a pinch of ginger to the rice when you take it off the stove. Sprinkle pistachios on top and serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Mushroom Shrimp Casserole recipe; Put the butter in the pan and melt it. Add the thinly sliced onion, green pepper and garlic and sauté. Then add the sliced mushrooms and cook until the water evaporates. Add the cleaned and washed shrimps to the pan and sauté. Peel and dice the tomatoes, then add them to the pan. After adding salt and pepper, cook for 10 minutes. After the cooking process is finished, put 4 shrimp in a stew, sprinkle the cheddar on it and put it in the oven. Wait until the cheddar cheese melts and take it out of the oven. Mushroom Shrimp Casserole is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Sinarit recipe; Chop the tomatoes into hazelnut size, finely chop the onion, garlic and parsley. Wash the fish and place on the baking tray. Cut the potatoes into half moons and cook them. After cooking, place the fish next to it. Lightly fry the onion and bay leaf in a pan with olive oil and add the flour, tomato, parsley and garlic and continue frying. Add 2 glasses of water and as much salt as you want. Pour this mixture that you have obtained on the fish in a way that it is everywhere. Place the tray in the oven and cook for about half an hour until all of the water has been absorbed. Sinarit is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the oven baked mackerel recipe; After washing the fish, cut the sides with a knife. Place the baking paper on the baking tray. Grate half of an onion, add 1 tablespoon of olive oil and salt into it. Pour this mortar over the fish. Chop the garlic and tomatoes into small pieces and add them to the fish. Slice the lemon into circles and top with the bay leaves. Finally, pour the remaining olive oil on top. Cover the tray with foil and put it in the preheated oven at 180 degrees. After half an hour, remove the foil on the tray and bake for another 20 minutes. Baked mackerel fish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the sponge cake recipe; Separate the 4 egg yolks and whites, put them in two separate bowls. Add half of the sugar to the bowl in which the egg white is put and beat with the help of a mixer until foamy. Add the remaining sugar to the egg yolk and beat with the help of a mixer. Then add the oil and boiling water to the container with the yolk, whisk again. After whisking well, add 1 packet of vanilla and 1 packet of baking powder to this mixture and whisk. Put the white of the egg, which is the yolk, with the help of a ladle and mix it gently. Grease the baking tray with butter, sprinkle 1 teaspoon of flour on top and spread it well with your hand, pour the remaining flour from the tray. Pour the ready-made coarse sponge cake dough and spread it well. Bake in the oven at 170 degrees for 20-25 minutes until the cake rises. Sponge Cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Fruit Cake recipe; first to prepare the sponge cake; Break 4 egg yolks and whites into separate bowls. Add half of 1 glass of sugar to the egg white and beat with the help of a mixer. Add the remaining sugar to the bowl with the egg yolk and whisk until it has the consistency of mayonnaise. Add half a glass of boiling water, 3 tablespoons of starch, 1 packet of vanilla, 1 packet of baking powder and 1 cup of flour to the bowl containing the egg yolk and whisk. After the beating is finished, slowly add the egg white to the bowl with the yolk and mix it with a wooden spoon. Pour the prepared dough into a greased and floured cake mold and bake for 20-25 minutes in a preheated oven at 170 degrees. For the cream; Put 3 glasses of milk, 4 tablespoons of granulated sugar, 2.5 tablespoons of flour, 1 tablespoon of starch, 2 packets of vanilla in a saucepan, cook on medium heat until it has the consistency of pudding. After cooking, take it off the stove and let it cool. After the cream has cooled, add 1 pack of whipped cream and beat with the help of a mixer. Preparation of fruit cake; Cut the sponge cake in half crosswise. Spread the cream on the first piece of the cake with the help of a spatula and chop the strawberries, bananas and kiwis and place them on the cream. Cover the remaining cake on it. Spread the remaining cream evenly on it. Garnish with fruits. Sprinkle powdered hazelnuts and coconut around the edges. Put the cake in the refrigerator for 2 hours to rest. Fruit cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Ravioli Sauce recipe; Melt the butter in the pan, add tomato paste and half a tea glass of hot water. Add red pepper and fry. Crush the garlic and mix it with yogurt. Ravioli sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the lasagna recipe; For the Meat Sauce; Add 3 tablespoons of oil to a large skillet. Add the diced onions and fry them. Add the ground beef after frying. After the minced meat is cooked, add the peeled, chopped tomatoes and garlic. After sautéing for about 10 minutes, add 2 tablespoons of tomato paste, about 1 glass of water and a dash of salt, take it off the stove and let it cool. For the Béchamel Sauce; Fry the butter and flour in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add milk slowly and stir constantly to avoid lumps. When it reaches the consistency of custard, remove it from the stove. After the minced meat sauce and béchamel sauce are prepared, grease a baking dish and arrange a layer of lasagna. Add the bechamel sauce first, then the minced meat mortar. Put the lasagna on it again. Repeat this process until the lasagna and sauces are gone. Add the remaining bechamel sauce and cheddar cheese on top of the lasagna. Wait 10-15 minutes for the lasagna to soften and then bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 15 minutes, wait in the oven until the cheddar is melted and browned. Lasagna is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Mantı Soup recipe; Boil the water and add salt and ravioli. Cook until the dumplings are soft. In another pan, fry the oil and tomato paste. Add the ground pepper and flour and fry for 1 minute. Add the boiled ravioli to the mixture along with the water. Add chickpeas and mint and bring to a boil. Ravioli Soup is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Cheese Pizza recipe; Mix honey, warm water and yeast and wait 10 minutes. Take the flour and salt in a deep bowl, add olive oil and knead and leave the dough for 30 minutes. Grate the tomatoes and garlic and cook for 3-4 minutes. Add tomato paste and thyme to the mixture. Divide the dough into 3 parts and roll out in a round shape. Place the dough on a baking tray with greaseproof paper, spread the sauce on the dough, sprinkle with grated cheese and leave 1 inch of space on the dough from the edges. Divide the dough into 4 equal parts and put in the oven at 250 degrees. Wait until it is browned and take it out in the oven. Cheese Pizza is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Lamb Cutlet recipe; Sprinkle the lamb with salt and cook on the oven grill until browned. After cooking, apply butter on them and wait for it to melt. Arrange the meat on the tray. Crush the garlic, mix with vinegar and add to the pan with the broth. Sprinkle powdered cloves, cumin, black pepper, cinnamon on top of the meat, and cook on a slow fire until the water is absorbed. Lamb Cutlet is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe for casserole beans; Boil the beans that have been waiting in water overnight and drain them. Finely chop the onion, peppers and tomatoes. Put the oil and onions in the pan and fry them. Add the tomato paste, tomato and pepper and cook by stirring. Add the beans and 6 cups of hot water and let it boil. Then add salt and bacon. Heat the casserole on the stove and place the mixture in the casserole while it boils. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 20 minutes. Dry beans in the casserole are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Dough Pastry recipe; First, grate the boiled potatoes in a bowl. Add the tomato paste and seasonings. On the other hand, mix the ingredients required for the sauce (1 egg, 4 tablespoons of yogurt, half a tea glass of oil, 2 tea glasses of water, salt). Grease the baking tray with oil and spread 1 piece of pastry on the tray. Pour the sauce you prepared in it all over the place. Put the potato mortar evenly all over the phyllo. Take the other phyllo and put it on top and repeat this process until the sauce and mortar are gone. After laying on the last sheet, fold the edges of the first sheet inwards. Add the last remaining sauce on it and bake in a preheated oven at 180 degrees for 20-25 minutes until golden brown. Dough Pastry is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Paçanga Pastry recipe; Add 1 teaspoon of oil to the pan. Add the diced peppers to the pan and sauté. After the peppers have cooled, prepare the stuffing by adding diced tomatoes, cheddar cheese and pastrami. Cut into 6-8 pieces depending on the size of the dough. Add a generous amount of the stuffing to each piece equally and wrap it in the form of a spring roll. Fry the prepared pastries in oil. Pacanga pastry is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Sour Eggplant recipe; Soak the multi-peeled and chopped eggplants in salted water for half an hour, then apply olive oil to the eggplants and fry them in the oven. Then chop the onions and fry them in a pan. Place the fried onions and eggplants on the tray. Add tomatoes, parsley, garlic, salt and water and close the lid. After cooking, add the lemon juice and remove from the stove. Eggplant with Sourdough is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For Dalyan meatball recipe; Take the ground beef in a deep bowl and add the stale bread that you soaked and squeezed. Grate the onion in a bowl, break 1 egg, add the spices and knead. Grease the baking tray and spread the prepared patties on the tray. Place the thinly sliced boiled carrots, 2 boiled peeled eggs in the length of the minced meat. Make the meat in the form of a roll and brush 1 egg on it with the help of a brush. Bake in a preheated oven at 170 degrees for 30 minutes. For the tomato paste sauce, mix the tomato paste, butter and water in the pan. Pour over the cooked meatballs and bake in the oven for another 5 minutes. Slice and serve with mashed potatoes on the side. Dalyan Meatballs is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Tantuni recipe; Chop 1 kg of lamb into cubes. Add vegetable oil to a large skillet and fry the meat until the water is gone. Finely dice the onion, tomato and pepper. Add the roasted meat to the tantuni lavash. Add tomatoes, onions, peppers and spices on top. Tantuni is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the acuka recipe; Fry the tomato paste with olive oil in a pan for five minutes. Put the spices and then the garlic in the tomato paste and fry for one more minute. Take the mixture off the stove and add the bread crumbs and ground walnuts and mix. After keeping the adjika at room temperature, take it to the refrigerator and let it cool down. Adjika is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal!

For the tahini bun recipe; Take water and milk in a bowl. Add the yeast and mix until it dissolves. Add sugar, salt and sunflower oil. Add the flour little by little and knead. When you get the consistency, cover it and leave it to ferment for about 40 minutes. Melt the butter in the pan. Add tahini to the melted butter and mix. Divide the fermented dough into equal portions and roll out thinly on a floured counter. Pour tahini on top, sprinkle with sugar and fold into quarters. Press and square each bundle you folded by hand and cut 2 cm strips. Grab and curl at the ends of the strips and wrap them around yourself. Place them on a greased paper-lined tray and press them lightly. Leave for 30 minutes in a warm place. Brush the egg yolk on top and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees until golden brown. Tahini bun is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Roast Beef recipe; Saute the diced onion and garlic in a frying pan with oil. Add the diced tomatoes and cook until it turns into a sauce. Add salt and pepper. Add oil to a different pan and fry the roast meat on the outside, turning it frequently. Then slice one inch apart. Put the meat in a baking dish and cover it with parchment paper. Bake in a preheated oven at 180 degrees for 35 minutes. Remove the parchment paper and bake for another 10 minutes. Take it in slices on a serving plate and pour the tomato sauce over it. Roast Beef is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Semolina Halva recipe; Bring the sugar and water to the boil in one pot, and boil the milk in another pot. In another pan, fry the oil and peanuts until they turn brown. Then slowly add the syrup and milk. Fry until the water is absorbed. Semolina Halva is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the egg bean recipe; Chop the beans into small pieces and soak them in hot water for 10 minutes and strain. Chop the onion into cubes and put the oil in a pan and fry the onions in the oil. When the onions turn pink, add the beans and continue frying. Finely chop the garlic and add the garlic. Lastly, add salt, pepper and paprika, break the eggs and turn off the heat when the eggs are cooked. Egg beans are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the pear jam recipe; Divide the pears into quarters and remove the cores. Put the pears in the pot, put lemon juice and sugar on it. Boil for 2 hours, first on high and then on low heat. Soak glass jars in hot water. Pour the jam into the jars while hot, close the lids tightly and turn them upside down. Once the jams have cooled, keep them in the refrigerator to cool completely. Pour into bowl when to be consumed. Pear jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For egg bean recipe; Peel and finely chop the onion, lightly fry with olive oil. Then add the boiled black-eyed peas and fry them. Beat the eggs with salt and pepper in a separate bowl, slowly add to the dish. When the eggs are cooked, take them off the stove. Egg beans are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Orange Jam recipe; Peel the oranges, chop them into small pieces and put them in a deep saucepan. Put plenty of water in the pot and boil for 15 minutes. Strain the juice from the boiling oranges and let them cool. Put sugar, 2 glasses of water, 1 glass of orange juice in a saucepan and bring to a boil. After adding the oranges to this pot, boil them for about 50 minutes until they get a thick consistency. Add the juice of half a lemon to the thickened syrup and boil for another 10 minutes. After boiling, put them in glass jars and close the lids after they cool. Orange Jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Pear Compote recipe; Wash and peel the pears. Slice and remove core parts. Put the pears, cloves, sugar and water in the pot and boil until the pears are soft. When it comes to room temperature, put it in the refrigerator. Pear Compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the apricot jam recipe; Cut the apricots at the midline and remove the seeds. Put the apricots in a deep saucepan. Pour 1 kg of sugar on it so that it covers all parts and wait for watering. Then cook it on high heat for the first 10 minutes, then on low heat until it reaches the consistency of jam. Remove the foam that comes out while cooking. Add the juice of half a lemon and boil for another 10 minutes. Take it off the stove and put it in jars, after it cools down pour it into glass jars and seal it. Pour into bowl when to be consumed. Apricot jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the apple jam recipe; Wash, peel and core the apples. Then slice and chop the apples into small pieces. Boil water and sugar in a saucepan. After boiling, add the lemon juice, cloves, cinnamon and apples to the pot. Keep boiling until the apples are soft. When it boils, turn off the heat and pour into glass jars. Close the lids when the jam has cooled. Pour into bowl when to be consumed. Apple jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the quince jam recipe; peel the quinces and cut them into cubes. Add water to a large pot and bring to a boil. After the water boils, add the quinces. Add the quince seeds. Quince seeds give color to the jam and give it consistency. After the quinces soften, add the sugar. Boil for another 20 minutes and add the lemon juice. Boil for another 2-3 minutes and remove from the stove. After it cools down slightly, put it in a jar and close the lids after it has cooled completely. Quince jam is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Curtain Pilaf recipe; Boil the chicken thighs. Add the margarine to the rice cooker and melt it. Wash the rice, drain and fry for 2-3 minutes in the pot. After adding the chicken stock and salt, close the lid. Take it off the stove before the rice is fully cooked. Peel the chickens. Add the shredded chicken, currants and black pepper to the rice and mix well. Making the dough; Knead the dough by mixing 2 eggs, 4 tablespoons of yoghurt, 100 g of melted margarine, 1 packet of baking powder and flour as much as possible. Divide the dough into two large and small parts. Open the larger one to 3 mm thickness and place it on the bottom of the bowl, covering the edges. Empty the rice inside. Open the small piece of dough and cover it to cover. Bake in an oven preheated to 200 degrees until golden brown. Curtain pilaf is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Chestnut Rice recipe; Peel the chestnuts. Boil in hot water so that it does not fall apart. Strain the chestnuts out of the water. Chop chestnuts the size of hazelnuts. Meanwhile, melt the margarine in a saucepan. Add the rice to the pot and fry for 5 minutes. Turn a few times after adding salt and chestnuts. Add the broth and close the lid. After the rice is cooked, turn off the stove and cover the bottom of the lid with a towel and wait for it to brew. Chestnut Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Chicken Pancake recipe; Whisk the flour, salt and eggs in a bowl, add the milk slowly and let it sit for 20 minutes. Oil the pancake pan and pour some of the mixture into the pan with the help of a ladle. Cook the crepes side by side. Add finely chopped onion and olive oil to a saucepan and fry. Add the diced chicken breast and fry it again. Add salt and pepper and let it cool. Place the pancakes in the baking dish by adding the stuffing in the middle of the pancakes and folding them. Grate the cheddar cheese on it and bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 30 minutes. Chicken Crepe is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Kumpir recipe; Boil the potatoes sparingly. Mix black pepper with olive oil, brush with potatoes and roast in the oven. After it comes out of the oven, cut a scratch on the neck and put butter in it in the middle, crush it. Add the ingredients and add the cheddar cheese last and wait a few minutes in the oven for it to melt. Kumpir is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the croissant recipe; Put warm milk, granulated sugar and fresh yeast in a deep bowl and mix. Put the flour in a large kneading bowl, open the middle, pour the yeast into it and mix with the help of your hand. Hold for 10 minutes. Then add all the remaining ingredients and knead until you get a soft dough. Cover the dough with a clean cloth and let it rest for about 40 minutes. When the dough is fermented, sprinkle flour on the counter and roll the dough with the help of a rolling pin. Spread the melted butter on it and fold the dough in half and roll it out again. Apply oil on it again and fold it in half again and open it. Then cut triangles from the dough and wrap them like a spring roll. Brush the egg yolks on it. Arrange on a baking tray and leave for 15 minutes. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 20-25 minutes until golden brown. The croissant is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Tray Kebab recipe; Finely chop the parsley, onion and pepper. Knead the minced meat with spices, place the minced meat on a 25-30 cm tray. Slice the tomato, onion and potato and put it on the ground meat, fry the oil and tomato paste, add it and put it in the oven at 200 degrees. Tray Kebab is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Chicken Croquette recipe; Boil the chicken and roast it, and then the onion, garlic and parsley. Take them all in a bowl and add 1 egg and spices to the bowl. Wet the stale bread and add it and knead it well. Add cheddar cheese and cut into walnut-sized pieces and shape into a cylinder. Then put it all in flour first, then egg, then breadcrumbs. Fry them all in oil. Chicken Croquettes are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For Onion Croquette recipe; Chop the onions into rings and separate the rings. Gently mix soda, milk, flour, baking soda and salt, dip the onion rings in the flour and then in the mixture and fry in oil. Onion Croquettes are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Kete recipe; First prepare the stuffing. Put butter in a large saucepan and melt it. After it melts, add the flour and mix. Turn off the stove when the flour is light brown. Put the coarse flour on a separate side. Sprinkle salt and mix. Open the middle in the shape of a pool. Add fresh yeast. Add the milk and whey. Add lukewarm water. After the yeast has melted, knead it until it has the consistency of an earlobe. Roll the dough. Put it in a bowl, stretch the top and leave it to ferment. Divide the fermented dough into balls. Makes about 10 meringues. Open the meringues in a round shape. Divide the stuffing equally in the middle of the meringues we have opened and close the dough at the end and roll it around itself. Lay the dough that you have given the shape of rose pastry on the baking tray. Brush the egg yolk with the help of a brush. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven until the tops are browned. Kete is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe; Roast the meat you cut into cubes in a deep pan. Add half of the rice you washed and drained without removing the meat from the pot. Arrange the fried potatoes, cut into rings, so that they cover the top of the rice. Add the remaining rice on it and distribute the butter in small pieces over the rice. Add salt and add water so that a finger goes over the rice. Cook covered on low heat without stirring until the rice is infused. After cooking, turn the pot upside down on a tray. Makbule meal is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the fajita recipe; Finely chop the steak and chicken, put them in a bowl and add the grated garlic, oil, vinegar and seasoning and marinate for 2 hours. Finely chop the peppers and onions and sauté in oil. Fry the marinated meat on both sides, divide it into two separate bowls and put the sautéed vegetables on the side. Fajita is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

Easter buns; Add the yeast to the warm milk and water mixture and dissolve. Add the flour to the bowl and open the middle like a pool. Add the yeast mixture, sugar, salt, egg, melted butter and 2 teaspoons mahaleb. Knead the ingredients until they get the consistency of dough. Cover it with a damp cloth and leaven until the dough rises twice. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts. Prepare rolls 20 cm long. Glue it together from one end and braid it in the form of a hair braid and combine it at the other end. Brush it with egg yolk and sprinkle with powdered hazelnuts. Bake in a preheated 170 degree oven for 35-40 minutes until golden brown. Easter Bun is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the tirit recipe; Fry the meat in oil in a pan, add 1 glass of water and cook. Toast chopped bread in the oven. Chop the parsley and onion, spread the bread in a large bowl and pour over the broth. Chop the garlic and mix it with the yogurt. Add it to the meat, then add the onions and garlic. Tirit is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the oven baked turkey recipe; First of all, thoroughly wash and drain the whole turkey you bought. Peel and grate the shallots separately. Peel and grate the garlic. Mix the water, garlic, onion, juice of 2 lemons, tomato paste, salt, pepper, thyme and sugar in a bowl. Pass the prepared sauce through a gauze strainer and add vegetable oil. Brush this sauce on the inside and outside of the turkey. Leave the turkey in the refrigerator overnight. The next day, grease the baking tray with oil and place the turkey on the baking tray. Chop the tomatoes and peppers to medium sizes and place them around the turkey. Brush the remaining onion sauce over the turkey again. Put the bay leaf in the turkey and cook it in the heated oven until it turns golden brown. Baked turkey is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Mafis Dessert recipe; Mix eggs, baking soda, yogurt, salt, oil and flour and knead. Cut the dough into walnut-sized pieces and roll it out one by one with a rolling pin. Cut into squares and tuck into a bow, then deep-fry. At the same time, boil sugar and water to make sherbet and cool it. Get the sweets in sherbet. Mafis Dessert is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Stuffed Turkey recipe; Put the well-washed turkey in a deep pot. Add the quartered onion, salt, pepper and bay leaf and cook well. On the other hand, put olive oil in the rice cooker and heat it, then add the rice and fry it. Add the pine nuts, currants, salt and pepper to the rice and fry it a little, then add the turkey's boiling water to just over the rice, close the lid and cook until it is infused. After the stuffing is done, place the turkey on the baking tray. Place the stuffing in the turkey and put the turkey in the oven. Cook until the top is golden brown. Turkey Stuffed is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Oğmaç Soup recipe; Mix flour, salt and water and knead. Sprinkle flour on the tray and spread the dough on the tray, boil milk and water in a saucepan. Add salt to the dough and rub it with your hands, put the dough into the boiling mixture and cook until soft. In a bowl, whisk the yoghurt and fry the oil, paprika and mint. And add them to the soup, too. Oğmaç Soup is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the creamy mushroom pasta recipe; Boil the pasta in 1.5 liters of salted water. While the pasta is boiling, wash and finely chop the mushrooms. Add oil to the Teflon pan, put the mushrooms and fry them. After the mushrooms have released their juices, add the cream and cook for a few more minutes. On the other hand, drain the pasta and return it to the pot. Add some olive oil and fry it on low heat. Add the creamy mushroom sauce and mix. Creamy mushroom pasta is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Creamy Chicken recipe; Finely chop the mushrooms and finely chop the chicken. Add the diced chicken and vegetable oil to a deep pan. After a few minutes on the first hot fire, cook it on low heat until the chickens absorb their water. When the chicken is done, add the mushrooms. In a different pan, cook the grated garlic and 1 pack of cream until it thickens. After it thickens, add it on top of the chickens and mix. Creamy Chicken is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Homemade Yogurt recipe; Put the milk in a pot with a lid, at a temperature that your finger can withstand, pour the whipped yogurt slowly over it, mix it once and close the lid of the pot. Cover it tightly with a thick cloth, leave it in a warm environment for 5-6 hours. Homemade Yogurt is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Milk Halva recipe; Melt the margarine in a pan and add the flour, fry the flour until it turns brown. Boil the milk in another pot, add it to the flour. Then add granulated sugar and vanilla and turn off the stove. Put the halva on the baking tray and keep it in the oven until golden brown, then slice it when it comes to room temperature. Milk Halva is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Flax Halva recipe; Boil water and sugar in a saucepan and pour it on a greased tray and wait until it becomes waxy, then fry the flour in oil and sift the roasted flour onto a tray. Scrape the sugar from the pan and make a ring shape by hand and place it on the flour. Pull on the 3 levers until it is stringy with the flour. Flax Halva is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Walnut Baklava recipe; First, to prepare the syrup, add sugar and water to the pot and boil it until it thickens slightly, and just before taking it off the stove, drip 1-2 drops of lemon juice and let it cool. For the dough; Put the egg, salt, milk and half a glass of water into the mixing bowl. Then slowly add the flour and wheat starch and knead until you get a dough that will not stick to the hand. After kneading the dough, make 24 small meringues. Open the meringues you have prepared with a rolling pin so that they are thin and round the size of a tray. Put 8 pieces of dough on the tray, one on top of the other. Then drizzle over half of the walnuts. Then put the 8 doughs you rolled out on top of each other and sprinkle the remaining walnuts on top of each other. Put the remaining 8 rolled dough pieces on top of each other. Then slice as baklava slices or as small squares. Melt the oil and butter in a pan over low heat. Pour the well-heated oil over the baklava. Then bake in the oven at 200 degrees for about 20-25 minutes until golden brown. Take the baklava out of the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes, then pour the cooled syrup over it. Walnut baklava is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the chocolate cake recipe; Cook the chocolate and cream in a saucepan over low heat, stirring, until the chocolate melts. Then let it cool in the fridge. Take the egg whites and sugar in a deep bowl and beat with a mixer until foamy. Then add the yolks and continue beating. Add the liquid oil on it and continue whisking so that the foam does not go out. After sifting the baking powder, half a pack of cocoa, flour and 5 grams of vanilla, add to the mixture and mix well. Grease the cake mold, pour the mixture and put it in the oven preheated to 180 degrees. Bake for 30-35 minutes until a toothpick comes out dry. To prepare the cream while the cake is baking, pass the room temperature oil well through the mixer and add the cream cheese, powdered sugar, 1 packet of vanilla, the remaining cocoa and milk, mix with the mixers and then let it rest. When the cake you baked has cooled, cut it in half. Spread all of the pastry cream on the first layer of the cake. Then cover the other layer on top and cover it all with the ganache you have cooled in the fridge. Chocolate cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Crying Cake recipe; First, beat the egg and sugar until foamy, then add 2 tablespoons of milk, flour, baking powder, cocoa and oil and mix. Pour the cake batter into the greased cake mold and bake in a preheated oven at 170 degrees until a toothpick comes out dry. Pour 2 cups of milk onto the first hot cake after piercing it with a toothpick. After the cake has completely cooled, apply the prepared whipped cream. Finally, pour plenty of chocolate sauce. Crying cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Risotto Recipe; Heat the chicken broth, finely chop the onion and garlic. Add the oil, onion, and garlic to the pot, and then add the rice and sauté until it turns brown. Add the vinegar and wait until it evaporates, Add salt and pepper and mix. Add the chicken broth and finally add the parmesan cheese and butter and let it rest for 10 minutes. Risotto is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the rusks recipe; Break the egg whites into a deep bowl and beat them with a mixer until foamy. Whisk the egg yolks and powdered sugar in a separate bowl. Knead the yolk and white of the eggs and all other ingredients until they reach the consistency of earlobes and form the dough. Pour the dough into a floured or greased cake tin. Bake in the oven at room temperature. Cut the cooked rusk into thin slices after leaving it for a day. Place the slices on a baking tray and bake until golden brown. Rusks are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the pesto sauce recipe; Wash and dry the basil well. Then peel the garlic. Put the pine nuts in the pan and roast them on medium heat until they change color. Add olive oil to the blender first, then garlic, basil, salt, pepper, grated parmesan and pine nuts, mix all the ingredients until they reach a liquid consistency. Take it on the serving plate. Pesto sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Paella recipe; Soak the squid and angler fish in milk the night before. Boil the head and bones of the anglerfish with salted saffron. Put oil and garlic in a large skillet. First, fry the shell prawns in the pan for 7-8 minutes. Then, turn the squid and lantern fish that you removed from the milk in a pan for 10 minutes. Add the cubed meat and chopped chicken. Add the mussels that you washed and dried well. Grate the tomato and add it to the pan. After washing and draining the rice, turn it in the pan with the other ingredients. Add salt, black pepper and red chili powder to taste. Mix half a liter of saffron fish stock with 1 tea glass of hot water and pour it into the pan. Close the lid of the pan and turn the heat down after it starts to boil. After some water remains, turn off the stove. Paella is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Boza recipe; Wash the bulgur and rice in a bowl, add plenty of water and boil it. Then pass it through a blender and strain in a fine strainer. When it is warm, add the yeast and add the granulated sugar. Boza is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Beyti Kebab recipe; grate the onion and garlic and put them in the bowl, then add the ground meat and spices and knead, divide the dough in half, add the mixture to each piece of dough, and fold it into a cylinder. Cut the phyllo diagonally with a knife and place on a greased baking tray. Bake in a preheated 200 degree oven until golden brown. Melt the butter, sunflower oil and tomato paste in the pan and pour over the kebab and serve yogurt on the side. Beyti Kebab is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the cheddar cheese pasta recipe; Fill a deep saucepan halfway with water and add 1 tablespoon of salt and oil. Put the pot on the stove and when the water boils, add the pasta. While the pasta is cooking, grate the cheddar cheese. When the pasta is swollen, cover and drain. Let it sit for a few minutes to drain in the strainer. While the pasta is well drained, put the deep pot on the stove, put the butter in it and melt it on low heat. When the butter melts, add the drained pasta to the pot and mix it a few times. After mixing, turn off the heat and add the grated cheddar cheese and mix a few more times. Distribute evenly on plates for 8 people. Pasta with cheddar cheese is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the tomato paste recipe; Fill a deep saucepan with half of water and add salt to it and put it on the stove. When the water boils, add the pasta and let it cook. While the pasta is cooking, add oil to a pan and heat it. When the oil is hot, add 1 teaspoon of salt, tomato and pepper paste and fry it for 2-3 minutes on low heat and turn off the heat. When the pastas swell, drain the pasta thoroughly with the help of a strainer. Then pour it back into the pot. Add the tomato paste you prepared on the pasta and mix until the paste is well dispersed. Pasta with tomato paste is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Spinach Potato Pie recipe; Wash the spinach in plenty of water and boil it in a deep pot. Put the potatoes in a separate pot, add enough water to cover them and put them on the fire to boil until they are soft. Chop the onions and fry them in oil. Add the tomato paste, salt and spices and keep stirring until the salami is browned. Add the boiled and drained spinach, mix a little and take it off the stove. Peel the skins off the potatoes and mash them in a tray with a fork. Add the mashed potatoes to the bowl where you added the spinach and mix. Cut a phyllo dough in half, spread a piece of it on the counter and apply oil on it with a brush. Place the spinach and potato mortar you prepared randomly on the dough. Start at the long edge and roll it up. Place the rolled roll on the greased baking tray, starting from the middle and wrapping it around. Crack the eggs in a bowl and when all the phyllo is done, brush scrambled eggs on the pastry and put it in the oven. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven until golden brown. Enjoy your meal.

For the spinach cabbage soup recipe; Wash the spinach and cabbage leaves in plenty of water and put them in a blender. Peel the onions, clean and finely chop the carrots. Heat the oil in a medium saucepan, add the onions and fry the onions. After the onions are roasted, add the carrots and fry them a little. Then add salt, pepper and milk and mix. Finally, add the spinach, cabbage and water you have passed through the blender and mix. Keep stirring for 15 minutes on low heat and turn off the heat. Spinach Cabbage Soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the spinach cheese quiche recipe; Wash the spinach in plenty of water and chop it for food. Onion thinly sliced. Add vegetable oil to a pan and fry the onions in the oil until golden brown. When the onions are roasted, drain them well, add the spinach, salt, pepper and fry the spinach. When the spinach is roasted, close the bottom of the pan and let it cool. Mash the feta cheese in a bowl with the help of a fork and add it to the spinach. In another bowl, put the melted margarine, yoghurt and break the eggs and whisk a little. Add the flour and baking powder to the dough and knead until you get a smooth dough. When the dough reaches the consistency that it will not stick to the hand, put it in my oiled heat resistant pan and press it to spread the dough to the sides of the pyrex. Pierce the dough in places with a fork. Spread the spinach mixture on it and add it. When the color of the dough starts to turn in a preheated oven at 180 degrees, bake it and sprinkle the cheddar cheese on it. After sprinkling with cheddar cheese, put it back in the oven and bake for another 2-3 minutes. Take it out of the oven when the cheese melts and turns colour. Spinach Cheese Quiche is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the spinach recipe; Wash and clean the spinach in plenty of water. Finely chop the onion, add the oil to a pan and fry the onions until they turn pink. Add the tomato paste and continue frying. Then drain and add the spinach thoroughly and fry until the spinach is melted. Wash half a tea glass of rice, drain the water thoroughly, add it to the spinach and mix. Finally, add salt, black pepper, red pepper flakes and 1 glass of boiling water and close the lid. Cook until the rice is soft. Turn off the heat when the rice is soft. Spinach dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the egg recipe with white cheese; Put the oil in the pan and melt it on low heat. Mash the feta cheese with a fork, add it to the pan and turn it 1-2 times. Crack the eggs on the cheeses and close the lid of the pan. Cook for about 3-4 minutes until the eggs are cooked and turn off the heat. Sprinkle the paprika on it. Eggs with white cheese is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the homemade noodle (egg) recipe; Put the eggs with milk in a deep bowl and beat them with the help of a mixer. Take the flour into the dough mixing bowl. Add salt and mix. Open the middle of the flour like a pool. Add the milk mixture. Knead until you get a smooth and non-sticky dough. Divide the dough into two equal parts. Transfer the dough to a baking paper lined tray. Cover it with a cloth and let it rest for 1 hour at room temperature. Take one of the doughs and roll it out to be a little thicker than the ready-made phyllo dough with the help of a rolling pin on the flour-sprinkled counter. Open the other dough in the same way and let it rest for 1 hour at room temperature by turning both sides once in a while. After you cut the phyllo in the way you want, bake it in the oven at 200 degrees. Store in a cool and dry place and consume whenever you want. Enjoy your meal.

For the homemade noodle (cooked) recipe; Put half of the water and sunflower oil in a deep saucepan. When the water boils, put the noodles in the water and boil them until they swell. After the noodles are boiled, drain them with the help of a strainer. Then put the butter in the same pot and melt it over low heat. When the butter melts, add the milk noodles and mix well to lubricate the noodles. Lastly, sprinkle salt and mix a few more times and close the bottom. Homemade noodles are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Roll Dough recipe; Put the hot water, dry yeast and sugar in a bowl and mix until dissolved. Set aside for about 5 minutes until bubbles form on it. Then add half a tablespoon of olive oil and salt, mix. Take the yeast mixture in a large bowl. Add 1/3 of the flour and mix with a spoon. Keep adding the flour gradually. When it reaches the consistency that it will not mix with a spoon anymore, take the dough on the floured counter and continue kneading with your hand. Add flour and continue kneading until you get a soft but non-sticky consistency. When you get the dough consistency, give it a ball shape and put it back in the bowl. Cover it tightly with cling wrap and let it rest for about 1-1.5 hours until it doubles in size. While the dough is resting, peel and core the tomatoes and dice them. Remove the seeds from the peppers and finely chop them. After resting the dough, take it back to the floured counter. Open it rectangular. Arrange the cheese on the entire surface, with the shortest part of the dough in front of you. Saute the peppers and tomatoes that you cut very small in olive oil very lightly and add them to the cheeses. Roll it up and place it on the baking tray. Rub the remaining olive oil all over with the help of a brush. Sprinkle the pepper thyme mixture on top. Then let it rise again for 1 hour. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for about 25-30 minutes until golden brown. Slice and serve after cooking. Cheese roll dough is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the walnut sausage recipe; Put the molasses and water in a deep pot and light the bottom. When the molasses and water mixture boils, take 1 cup of the mixture and slowly add the flour and starch in a bowl and whisk. Keep whisking until there are no lumps. Then pour the sugar into the boiling molasses water. Slowly add the mixture you prepared with flour and starch into the boiling molasses water. Keep mixing until you get a creamy consistency. When it boils, turn off the heat and thread the walnuts through the middle of the quilt yarn. Dip the walnuts you put on the thread into the pot and take them out and hang them in a suitable place. After waiting for 2 days, wrap it with cling film. You can keep it for about 3-4 months. Enjoy your meal.

For the stuffed peppers recipe; wash the peppers. Cut off your stems. Cut off the top of the peppers so that the lid does not come off completely. Clean them up. To prepare the stuffing, grate the tomatoes and onions, wash and finely chop the parsley. Put the minced meat in a deep bowl. Add the rice, 2 tablespoons of oil, salt, pepper, grated tomato and onion mixture on it and mix well. Stuff these stuffed bell peppers. Knee in the pot. Add half of the water and cook on low heat until the rice is cooked. Serve hot. Stuffed peppers with minced meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the vegetable soup recipe with minced meat; First of all, peel the carrot, tomato, onion, green pepper, peel and chop the potato into small pieces. Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the onions and fry them. After the onions, put the carrot in order, turn it a little, and add the potato, pepper and minced meat. Then add the tomato and fry a little more, then add the flour and tomato paste and mix. After stirring for a few minutes, add the water and boil until the vegetables are cooked. When the vegetables are cooked, add the noodle and cook for another 5 minutes and turn off the heat. Vegetable soup with minced meat is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe for tarhana soup with minced meat; Soak the tarhana in 1 glass of warm water in a bowl. Melt the butter in a saucepan, Chop the onions for cooking and add to the oil and fry. After frying the onions a little, add the tomato paste and fry for a few more minutes. After frying the tomato paste a little, add the chili pepper and mix. Then add the minced meat and continue frying until cooked. When the minced meat is cooked, add the tarhana and water and mix until it becomes a thick consistency. Add salt at the end and cook for a few more minutes. Tarhana soup with minced meat is ready to serve. Health. let it be.

For the leaf wrap recipe with minced meat; Soak the rice in hot water for 15 minutes before cooking. Soak the fresh leaves in boiled water for 4-5 minutes and let them drain in a strainer. Chop the onion and parsley for food. Drain the rice water and put the rice, minced meat, onion, tomato paste, 1 teaspoon salt and spices in a wide and deep bowl and knead. Take the vine leaf in your palm with the matte and veined part facing towards you and wrap it with a teaspoon of minced meat. Do the same with the other leaves. Place the wrapped dolms in a deep pot so that there are no gaps. Peel the skin of the tomato and grate it. Saute the grated tomato in half a glass of vegetable oil, then add 2 glasses of water and 1 teaspoon of salt and mix. Cook for another 2-3 minutes, take it off the stove and pour it over the stuffing. Cover a porcelain plate by turning it upside down so that the leaves do not open during cooking. Cook on medium heat with the lid closed until the rice swells. Leaf wrap with minced meat is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe for kemalpaşa dessert with tahini; Boil water and 1 cup of sugar in a saucepan and turn off the heat. Throw in the kemalpasa and cook it. For her keenness, pour the milk into a saucepan. Add the remaining granulated sugar, starch, flour, vanilla and ground almonds. Mix it with a whisk, cook it until it reaches a thick consistency and turn off the heat when it boils. Place the softened kemalpaşa desserts in a glass baking dish. Pour the tahini on top of it, and then pour the cake you cooked on it. Serve when cool. Kemalpaşa dessert with tahini is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the chard roll pastry recipe; Wash the chard in plenty of water and finely chop the onion and garlic. Add olive oil to a pan and heat it. Once the oil is hot, add the onion and garlic and fry. Add the chard and cook until the chard is soft. Finally, add salt and pepper and set aside to cool. When it cools down, add the labneh cheese and mix it well. Assemble the dough on the floured counter. Wrap the chard dough on the dough as a roll of spring dough. Cut the dough into slices, lay them on the baking tray and bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Charcoal roll pie is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Italian firttata recipe; peel the onions and cut them into thin strips. Then peel the potatoes and cut them into small cubes. Trim the parsley and cut it thinly, then slice the sun-dried tomatoes and mushrooms into thin strips. Wash small tomatoes (cherry tomatoes). Chop the spinach with half of your hands. Heat the oil in a deep-sided pan that can go into the oven, then add the onions and potatoes and cook until they change color. Add dried tomatoes and mushrooms and fry a little. Add the small tomatoes and spinach and mix. Beat the eggs in a separate bowl with salt, pepper and finely chopped parsley. Pour the egg over the sautéed mixture in the pan. Make sure that the egg is evenly distributed and that the small tomatoes are on top. Bake in a preheated oven at 180 - 200 degrees until it puffs up. You can take it out of the oven and slice and serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the milk spread pastry recipe; Whisk the egg, oil, milk and salt in a deep bowl. For the stuffing, finely chop the parsley and add a teaspoon of salt with the cheeses. Grease the baking tray where you will put the pastry. Place half of 1 phyllo on the bottom of the tray. Dip out the remaining phyllo in the sauce you prepared and lay it out on the dry phyllo. Place 1 more phyllo in this way and sprinkle half of the cheese mixture on the phyllo. Again, lay the half dry dough on the cheese mixture, dip the other half in the sauce and place it. After placing the remaining stuffing and dipping the remaining phyllo in the sauce, pour the remaining sauce over the pastry. Bake in a preheated oven at 180 degrees until golden brown. Bread with milk sprinkles is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the German cake recipe; First of all, for the cream, mix 3 cups of milk, 1 egg, 3 tablespoons of flour, 1 tablespoon of starch in a whisk without putting it on the fire. Then turn on the fire and whisk with the whisk until the eyes are eye to eye. Take it from the stove, add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 tablespoon of butter and leave it to cool on one side. For the sponge cake; Whisk the remaining eggs and sugar in a bowl until foamy. Add oil, milk and yogurt and mix slowly. Then add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and continue beating. Grease a round tray with a diameter of 25 cm and sprinkle a little flour on it. Pour the dough you prepared on the tray and bake in the oven at 160 degrees for about 50 minutes. After the time is up, take the cake out of the oven, divide the cake in half horizontally and apply the cream you prepared in the middle. Cover the cake and sprinkle powdered sugar on it for the last time, according to your preference. German cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the olive oil celery recipe; Cut the celery into medium-sized pieces, the potatoes into cubes, and the carrots into rounds. Finely chop the onion and add a little salt and rub until the water comes out. Put the oil in the bottom of the pan and put the celery, potatoes, carrots and onions on it, and cook it for 5 minutes on low heat. Squeeze the lemon with one hand. Put the water, lemon juice, sugar, salt and whole wheat flour in a deep bowl and mix it well. Pour the lemon sauce you prepared over the vegetables. Cook until the vegetables are soft. When the fork begins to sink easily into the vegetables, turn off the heat and let it cool. Divide on plates when cool. Celery with olive oil is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the spicy chicken recipe in the oven; First, grate the onion and garlic into a coarse bowl, add 1 tablespoon of yoghurt, 1 tablespoon of tomato paste, 3 tablespoons of oil, black pepper, cumin, thyme and chili flakes and mix well. Then clean the chickens elsewhere and cut off the excess skin, making scratches on it so that it cooks well. Spread the sauce you prepared generously on the chickens. Put the chickens on the baking tray and put them in the oven. Bake in a preheated 200 degree oven until golden brown. Spicy chicken in the oven is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the chicken skewer recipe; Cut the chicken breasts into squares. Prepare the sauce by mixing olive oil, milk, yogurt, tomato paste, thyme, salt and chili pepper. After keeping the chicken meats in the sauce you prepared for at least 1 hour, line up the bottles. Bake in an oven at 220 ºC until lightly pink. Enjoy your meal.

For the chicken drumstick recipe with baked potatoes; peel, wash and cut the potatoes into finger shapes, peel the onions and cut them into rings. Clean and wash the chicken drumsticks. In a deep wide bowl, put the pepper, salt, thyme, chicken thighs and potatoes and mix. Pour the blended chicken and potatoes onto the baking tray. Add tomato paste, onion, water and oil to another bowl and mix. Pour this mixture over the chicken and potatoes on the baking sheet. Bake the chicken with potatoes in the oven at 180 degrees until golden brown. Chicken drumstick with baked potatoes is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the chicken snitzel recipe; Cut the chicken breast lengthwise into medium thickness and wash it well. Leave the washed slices in the strainer to drain. After the water is drained, dip it in flour from front to back, shake it a little and let the excess flour spill. Crack the eggs into a wide, flat plate. Put the meat completely covered in flour and drained of water into the egg, shake it a little to allow the excess egg to flow. Then, dip it in the breadcrumbs you prepared, and pat the chickens you find lightly to ensure that the breadcrumbs stick to the meat. Take the oil in the pan and heat it well. Cook the chickens until they are golden brown on both sides. Chicken snitzel is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For boiled chicken leg recipe; First clean the chickens, put them in a saucepan and cook on high heat for 5 minutes. Peel and wash the potatoes. Cut the potatoes into 4 pieces and put them in the chicken in the pot. Peel the onion and put it whole in the pot. Add enough water to the pot to cover the chickens. Add salt. Cook for 25 minutes on medium heat with the lid closed. Your boiled chicken leg is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the pizza (meat) recipe; First, combine yeast, salt, water and flour to knead and make dough. Wait until it ferments. Boil 3 grated tomatoes, 1 tablespoon of hot ketchup, 1 clove of crushed garlic, salt, olive oil, thyme and basil in a stove and then take it off the heat when it turns into a thick sauce. Finely chop the meat and cook it in its own juice. Spread the fermented dough on the tray. Spread the tomato sauce that we kept on the side, then sauté and blend the meat that we cut into smaller pieces on the side with green peppers a couple of times, then spread it evenly on the pizza dough we sauced. Put the pizza in the oven first so that the dough is partially cooked. Grate the cheese. Put it on the pizza. Finally, put it in the oven. Remove from the oven after the edges are browned. Let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Pizza (with meat) is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the grilled bonito recipe; Cut off the head of the acorn, cut open the abdomen and clean it. Cut into thick slices. Rinse in plenty of water to drain blood and dry with paper towels. Sprinkle salt on the bonito slices and arrange them on the grill intermittently. Rub olive oil between and on them and cook by turning them back and forth. Peel the onion. Then slice another coarse tomato, onion and lemon into rings and grill them. Serve these vegetables alongside the bonito. Grilled bonito is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the steamed bonito recipe; Cut off the head of the acorn and clean the belly by cutting open it. Wash in plenty of water and remove excess water with a paper towel. Peel the onion. Chop the tomatoes into cubes and the onions into half moons. Chop the parsley with a knife. Cut the lemon into rings. In a bowl, mix the tomato, parsley, pepper, onion with salt and pepper in a bowl. Put oil in the pan and spread it. Arrange the bonito slices on it. Put the tomato, onion, parsley mixture and 1 tea glass of water on it. Arrange lemon slices on it. It will be cooked on the stove for half an hour on low heat. Bonito is ready to be steamed. Enjoy your meal.

For the grilled salmon recipe; Put the lemon juice in a large bowl. Grate the garlic into this bowl. Add salt and pepper to the bowl as well. Finely chop the parsley and add it to the bowl and mix well with the other ingredients. Rub the salmon slices well into this mixture and leave it in the fridge for 1 hour. Then grill the fish until brown on both sides. Grilled salmon is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the vegetable frying recipe; Peel and dice the eggplants and potatoes, and cut the peppers into medium pieces. Put the oil in a deep Teflon pan and heat it. Put the potatoes in the oil you have heated and fry them first. When it is browned, place it on a wide plate lined with a napkin with the help of a strainer. Then put the eggplants and peppers in the same way and fry them too and put them on the plate. Put the oil on a napkin, put the pheasant vegetables on a napkin-less serving plate. To prepare the vegetable sauce, grate the tomatoes and garlic. Put 1 tablespoon of olive oil, garlic, salt, tomatoes in a small pan and cook. Pour the prepared sauce over the vegetables. Vegetable fry is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the summer vegetable soup recipe; Melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Fry the onions for 5 minutes until soft. Add the potatoes and carrots to the onions, fry a little, then add hot water and cook on low heat for 40 minutes. After the vegetables in the pot soften, add the cut tomatoes, corn kernels, peas and spinach leaves and cook for 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper. When serving, garnish with a mixture of freshly chopped herbs. Summer vegetable soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the cauliflower recipe; Add the oil to the pan and fry the finely chopped onions until they turn pink. Peel the carrots and add the carrots that you cut into rings to the pot and fry for a while with the onions. Add the tomato paste, after the paste is roasted, add the cauliflower flowers that you have cleaned and divided into the pot. After mixing the ingredients, add enough hot water to cover it and cook it on low heat until the cauliflower softens. Cauliflower dish is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the potato chips recipe; peel and wash the potatoes. Slice into thin round shape. Fill a wide and deep bowl with plenty of water, add salt and mix it. Drop the potatoes into the salt water. Take the starch-free potato in a strainer and strain it. Heat the oil in the frying pan. Throw the drained potatoes into the hot oil and fry for 1-2 minutes until the potatoes turn yellow and hard. Take the fried chips on a paper towel lined plate and absorb the oil. Serve salted. Potato chips are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the potato pancake recipe; Put the yogurt, olive oil and egg white in a deep bowl and whisk well with a whisk. Add the room temperature butter and beat some more. Add the flour and baking powder little by little and knead until you get a very soft dough. Cover it for 30 min. rest. Meanwhile, boil the potatoes and grate them, add salt, black pepper and red pepper and mix. Take some large pieces of walnut from the dough and open them in your hand. Put the potato stuffing in the middle, close and roll it. Mix the egg yolk with 1 teaspoon of oil in a plate and brush it over the pastries. Garnish the buns with black cumin. Place the prepared pastries on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven until it turns orange. Potato pancakes are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the farm meatball recipe; Beat the garlic, grate the onions and finely chop the parsley. Put the ground meat, crumbled bread crumbs, crushed garlic, grated onions, spices and half of the finely chopped parsley in a bowl and knead. Rest in the refrigerator for 15 minutes. Then break off walnut-sized pieces and roll them into shape by pressing lightly. Melt the margarine in a pan and fry the meatballs in this oil. Peel and clean the carrots, zucchini, potatoes and green peppers and cut them into the size of meatballs. Fry these chopped vegetables in oil after the meatballs. Peel and dice the tomatoes. Put your fried vegetables, meatballs, chopped tomatoes and peas in a pot and add 4 glasses of hot water, salt, pepper, oil and thyme and cook on low heat. Finely chop the dill and parsley and add them 1-2 minutes before closing the bottom of the pot and boil a little more. Then close the bottom of the pot and divide the meatballs on the serving plates. Farm meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For Tekirdag meatball recipe; Take the ground beef in a bowl, wet the bread, add the spices and knead for 5 minutes. Then grate the onion and garlic with the thin part of the grater, add them and continue kneading again. Finally, add an egg, semolina and carbonate and continue kneading again for 10 minutes. Cover with cling film and rest in the refrigerator for at least one night or a day. The next day, form thin and long shapes and cook in a fireproof skillet or on the grill. Tekirdag meatballs are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the wholemeal carrot cake recipe; First, break the eggs into a deep bowl and then add the granulated sugar. Beat with a mixer at high speed for approximately 5 minutes. Then add the vanilla, milk and oil and beat for another 2 minutes. Peel the carrots and grate coarsely. Add the last remaining ingredients and continue whisking to make the cake batter. Pour the prepared cake batter into the cake mold and put it in the preheated oven at 175 degrees. Bake for 25-30 minutes. Whole wheat carrot cake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the carrot dessert recipe; First, wash and peel the carrots, then grate them into a saucepan. Add sugar and water to these carrots and cook until the carrots are soft. Meanwhile, crush the starch with a small amount of water. Then slowly add the mashed starch with little water into the cooking carrot. After adding the starch slowly, let it cook for 1-2 more minutes and turn off the heat. Carrot dessert is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

Apricot Gummy Custard, pour the milk into a saucepan. Mix all other ingredients except apricot in a bowl. Finely chop the apricots and boil until soft. Slowly add the other ingredients to the milk. Turn off the bottom when the pudding thickens and does not slip. Sprinkle cinnamon to garnish. Apricot mastic custard is ready. Enjoy your meal.

For the cocoa cake recipe; Take the egg into the whisk, add the sugar and start whisking with the help of a mixer. After whisking, first add the oil and then the milk. Mix again for 1 minute. After this process, add the flour into the bowl. Next, add the cocoa, vanilla and baking powder. Keep beating. Once it has thickened, pour it into a greased mold. Leave the cake to bake in a preheated 180 degree oven. Cocoa Cake is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Ashura recipe; Soak the wheat and dried beans in hot water the night before. Soak the chickpeas in hot water. Change the water of the chickpeas and boil for 1 hour. Change the water of the dried beans and boil them for 15 minutes. Chop the figs into small pieces and boil them in water and strain the water. Boil the currants for 5 minutes and strain the juice. Chop the apricots into small pieces and boil them in 2 glasses of water until they swell (do not pour the juice). Wash the wheat in plenty of water and drain the water. Put the wheat, boiled chickpeas and boiled dried beans in the pressure cooker. Add 7 glasses of water into it and boil for 30 minutes. Pour the ingredients boiled in the pressure cooker into the pot. Then add 7 glasses of water again and boil it for another 15 minutes on medium heat. Then add powdered sugar and boil. When the cooking time is 50 minutes, add the milk, figs and orange zest and mix. When the boiling time is 1 hour, add the grapes and remove from the stove. Divide the Ashura into bowls. Garnish them with walnuts, pomegranates, hazelnuts and cinnamon and serve. Ashura is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the meringue recipe; Put egg white in a deep bowl, add a pinch of salt and beat with a mixer until foamy. Add the sugar little by little without stopping the mixer and continue to beat for 10 minutes (it should be thick and bright in color). Put the prepared mixture in a piping bag with a star tip and squeeze it on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. Bake in a preheated oven at 100°C. The meringue is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the wholemeal white cheese toast recipe; Warm the bread in the toaster. Then place one of the tomato slices on top of one of the bread slices. Place the feta cheese on top of the tomato slice. Put the remaining tomato slice on top of the cheese. Finally, put the other slice of bread on top and press down lightly. Cook the toast you prepared in the toaster until the cheese melts. Wholemeal white cheese toast is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the sweetened milk flour halva recipe; Take the cold milk into a bowl and melt the sweetener in it. Melt the butter in a pan and add the flour. Fry on low heat until it turns dark. At this stage, add the milk syrup and cook by mixing until it reaches a consistency that does not stick to the spoon. Turn off the heat when it reaches non-sticky consistency. Milky flour halva with sweetener is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the walnut cookie recipe; Put the egg, margarine, oil, powdered sugar in a bowl and mix well. Put the flour, baking powder, cocoa, walnuts in it and knead. Break off small pieces of walnuts from the dough and shape the dough into a round shape with your hands. Place the cookies you have shaped on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. Bake in a preheated 175°C oven for 10-15 minutes until golden brown. After cooking, arrange the cookies on the serving plate. If you wish, sprinkle powdered sugar on the walnut cookies. Your walnut cookies are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the apricot compote recipe; Wash the apricots thoroughly. Divide it into 2 and remove the cores. Put sugar in 6 glasses of water and boil it. Then add the apricots and boil for another 5 minutes. If the apricots are not soft, boil for another 5 minutes. Turn off the stove and add the cinnamon sticks and cloves. Leave the pot to cool with the lid closed. Once it's warm, put it in the fridge and let it cool. Apricot compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the ring dessert recipe; First, put the water in the pot to prepare the syrup. Add sugar to it and mix. After boiling, add the lemon juice and mix. Turn off the heat and let it cool. After leaving the syrup to cool on the side, put 2 glasses of water in a pot for the dough and boil it. Throw the butter on it. After it melts, add the flour and mix well. Keep it aside to cool. After the dough is warm, add the semolina and starch and knead. Add the eggs one at a time. Keep kneading until smooth. After the dough is well kneaded, give it a ring shape. Meanwhile, heat the oil in a saucepan. When the oil is hot, throw the rings into the oil and fry them. Immediately dip the fried sweets in cold syrup and arrange them on the serving plate. The ring dessert is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the recipe for dried apricot compote; Wash the apricots well. Put it in a bowl. Add hot water and let it sit for 4-5 minutes. Get a strainer and strain the water. Add the apricots, sugar and water into the pot. Boil on high heat first. Then cook on medium low heat until the apricots are soft. Add cinnamon sticks and cloves in it. Let it cool at room temperature. Then put it in the fridge to cool. Dried apricot compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the raisin compote recipe; If the grapes have trash, sort them out. Put the grapes in a bowl and add water to cover them and leave for 5 minutes. After waiting, drain the water and put the grapes in a pot. Add 6 glasses of water to the pot. Boil on high heat first. After boiling, reduce the heat and cook for another 15 minutes. Add half a glass of sugar. Cook for another 5 minutes and remove from the heat. Let it cool at room temperature and then put it in the fridge. Raisin compote is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the sweetened apple pudding recipe; Peel and dice the apples. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of powder sweetener on a Teflon pan and cook it so that it does not fall apart. Arrange apples in a high-sided bowl or single-serving bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon. Put the milk, flour, egg, powdered sweetener and vanilla in a deep saucepan and cook, stirring with wire, until it reaches the consistency of custard. Pour the custard you have obtained by pouring it over the apples. Then when it cools down, put it in the fridge. Sweetened apple pudding is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the prune compote recipe; wash the prunes and put the pot with the water. Boil the prunes until they swell. After 10-15 minutes, add the sugar. After boiling for another 10 minutes, turn off the heat and wait for it to warm up. Leave it to cool in the fridge. When cool, divide into bowls. Prune compote is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the chocolate pudding recipe; Put the milk, flour, cocoa, chocolate and sugar in the saucepan. Stir and cook until thickened. Add vanilla and butter and mix well. Cook on low heat for another 5 minutes, stirring. Take it from the stove. Fill into bowls while hot, and optionally decorate after cooling. Rest in the refrigerator for up to 3 hours. Chocolate pudding is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the home-grain bread recipe; Take wheat flour, rye flour, oat flour, bran and yeast into the mixing bowl and mix. Add sunflower seeds, pumpkin seeds, flax seeds, oat and sesame seeds. Knead by adding water little by little. Oil a large bowl and put the dough you prepared in this bowl and cover it with cling film. The dough is fermented at room temperature until it doubles in size. After it is fermented, knead it on a floured surface and give it a rectangular shape. Grease a rectangular non-stick bowl and place the prepared dough in it. Cover it with a damp cloth and leave it in the mold for 30 minutes. Bake in a preheated oven set at 180 degrees, by inserting a knife from time to time and checking. If the knife comes out clean, it is cooked. Slice the cooled bread. Grain home bread is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the oven-baked halva recipe; into a bowl, break the halva with your hand. Add the milk to the bowl, feed it to the halva. Add lemon juice and butter and mix until homogeneous. Pour the mortar into the oven dishes to a thickness of 1-2 cm. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 6-8 minutes. Wait for a while until it warms up. Halva in the oven is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the apple compote recipe; Peel and dice all the apples and put them in a saucepan. Add cold water and boil until apples are cooked. After cooking, add sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice. Boil for another 5 minutes and then remove from heat. After cooling, divide the apple compote into bowls. Apple compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the cherry compote recipe; Wash the cherries and remove the stems and drain. Put the water and granulated sugar in a saucepan and put it on the stove to boil. After the water and sugar have boiled, add the cherries to the pot, stir and boil for another 10 minutes. Take the curdled cherry compote from the stove, close the lid of the pot and keep it aside to cool. After the cherry compote has cooled, put it in the refrigerator and distribute it into bowls after it has cooled. Cherry compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the hamburger recipe; First, prepare the hamburger buns. For the hamburger buns; Put the flour, yeast, margarine, water, sugar and salt in a deep bowl and knead well. Make the dough soft. Then roll it into a ball and wrap it with cling film. Turn the oven to 50 degrees and let the dough rise for 30 minutes. Pour the fermented dough onto the floured counter, divide it into 8 equal parts and roll them. Grease the baking tray and place it on it. Bake in the oven at 160 degrees until the top is golden (20-25 minutes). Take it out of the oven and let it cool. For the meatballs; Take the ground beef into the mixing bowl. Add the parsley and spices to it. Add the onion and garlic by grating and knead well. After keeping it in the refrigerator for 15-20 minutes, divide it into 8 equal parts. Cook front to back in a pan without oil. Put the meatballs between the breads you baked. Serve with lettuce, tomato and pickled cucumbers on top of the meatballs. Hamburger is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the cheese burger recipe; Take the chicken mince in a large bowl. Grate the onion and garlic. Finely chop the parsley. Add the onion, garlic, breadcrumbs, pepper, thyme, black pepper and parsley to the chicken mince and yoghurt well. Cut into 4 equal portions the size of a hamburger patty. Cook on both sides in a pan without oil. Arrange the meatballs you cooked on the bottom layer of hamburger buns. Place cheddar cheese slices on it. Put the lettuce leaves on the cheese. Cut the tomato into thin rings and place the tomato slices on the lettuce leaves. Cover the top of the bread and place the hamburgers on the serving plates. Cheese burger is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the peach compote recipe; Peel the peaches, remove the seeds and cut into large cubes. Put the water, sugar and cloves in a saucepan. Stir on medium heat. After the sugar has melted, let it boil. When the water boils, add the chopped peaches and continue boiling for 10-12 minutes. When the peaches are soft, turn off the heat and remove from the stove. Keep it at room temperature and then put it in the refrigerator to cool. Divide the cooled peach compote into bowls. Peach compote is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the cherry compote recipe; Wash and drain the cherries. Put the water in the pot and boil it. Throw the cherries into the boiling water and cook for 5 minutes on low heat. Add sugar and mix. After boiling for 3 minutes, remove the pot from the stove. After keeping it at room temperature, put it in the refrigerator to cool. Cherry compote is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the chestnut starch cookie recipe; First of all, to prepare chestnut puree, draw the chestnuts, add enough water to cover them and boil them for about 30 minutes until they are soft. Before the boiled chestnuts get cold, thoroughly clean their shells and dice. Put the chestnuts, 1\2 glasses of hot water and sugar in a small saucepan and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Continue cooking while stirring the water. After it is well cooked, turn off the heat and mash it well with the help of a fork. Beat room temperature butter, sugar and egg yolk until creamy. Then add 4 tablespoons of the chestnut puree you prepared and continue whisking again. After the ingredients are thoroughly mixed, sift the starch, baking powder and flour, add them to the mixture and knead until it does not stick to the hand. Then keep it in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes by wrapping it in cling film. Take walnut-sized pieces from the dough you rested and put a teaspoon of chestnut puree between the palm of your hand and lightly open it and close it on both sides. Lay the cookies you prepared on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper, spaced apart. Bake in the preheated oven at 180 degrees for about 20-25 minutes until golden brown. Chestnut starch cookies are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the sardine pancake recipe; Put 1/2 cup of flour, starch, salt and mineral water in a deep bowl and mix without whisking. Add the egg yolks to this bowl and keep the bowl aside. Put the sunflower oil in a deep pan and heat it. Place the remaining 1/2 cup of flour on a large plate. Pour the breadcrumbs into another large bowl. Dip the half sardines first in the flour, then in the egg mixture, and finally in the breadcrumbs, then fry them in hot oil until they turn golden brown. Place the fried sardines on the serving plate by draining the oil with a slotted ladle. After applying the process to all sardines, the sardines are ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the milk soup recipe; Wash the rice and put it in the pot, add the water and boil it. Add the milk and salt to the boiled rice and bring it to a boil. In a separate place, melt the butter and add the red pepper flakes and fry. Pour the chili pepper butter into the soup and mix. Milk soup is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the fresh fruit mix compote recipe; boil sugar and water. Peel and dice the pineapple, pear, peach and kiwi. Separate the grapes from the bunch. Cut the apricots in half and remove the seeds. Add the fruit to the boiling syrup. Cook for 2-3 minutes and remove from the stove. Put the compote you prepared in a large glass bowl and let it cool. When it cools down, the compote of fresh fruit mix is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the fruit cake recipe; Chop the fruit into cubes. Crack the eggs into the whisk. Pour the powdered sugar over it and beat with a whisk until frothy. Then add the oil and milk and whisk again until the ingredients are mixed. Immediately after that, pour the vanilla, baking powder, flour and the dried fruits that you cut into cubes at the beginning. Beat for 8-9 minutes until everything is completely mixed. Then grease the cake mold and pour the mixture into the mold and bake the cake in the oven at 165 degrees. Fruitcake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the beef soup recipe; Chop the veal into cubes, add the water, put it in the pressure cooker and cook it until it gets soft. For its dressing, take the flour, yoghurt, egg yolk, salt and lemon juice in a bowl, whisk and strain.
