Heat a non-stick skillet over very low heat. Add a pinch of olive oil and a pinch of honey before putting the cheese balls in the pan. Then rotate the cheese balls constantly to make sure they are cooked evenly and remove from the heat before they lose their shape. Wash the greens you will use thoroughly, dry them and put them in a large salad bowl. Then add the cooked cheese balls, blueberries and sauce. Mix all the ingredients. Goat Cheese and Blueberry Greens Salad is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Eggplant and Chickpea Salad recipe; preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Place 1 cm thick slices of eggplant on the baking tray, brush both sides of the slices with olive oil. In a small bowl, mix the smoked paprika, cumin, cayenne pepper and a pinch of salt. Sprinkle the drained chickpeas on the eggplant slices on the baking tray. Cook the eggplant and chickpea mixture for about 30 minutes, flipping until browned and tender. Five minutes before removing from the oven, add the cherry tomatoes, cut into 2 or 4, depending on the size. Mix the yogurt and garlic in a bowl, then add the spices you combined earlier to this mixture. After the eggplant, chickpeas and tomatoes are cooked, combine them on a plate. Apply some oil on it. Season with pomegranate, coriander and spices and serve with the yogurt sauce you prepared. Eggplant and Chickpea Salad is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Carrot and Lentil Salad recipe; preheat the oven to 220 degrees. After rinsing the lentils, gently cook them in a pan for about 20 minutes, drain and set aside. Cut the carrots into pieces of medium thickness, about 3 centimeters long. Heat the coconut oil in a pan, pour it over the carrots and make sure they are completely covered with oil. Transfer the mixture to an ovenproof bowl and sprinkle the chopped coriander stalks with a pinch of salt. Bake in the oven for about 30 minutes, until the carrots are slightly tender. Take the carrot mixture out of the oven into a bowl. Add lentils, coriander leaves and vinegar and mix well. Sprinkle pine nuts on it and serve with wholemeal bread if you wish. Carrot and Lentil Salad is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Mushroom and Leek Tofu recipe; Drain the tofu and cut into cubes. Cook in olive oil for 8-10 minutes with grated lemon peel, garlic and tofu. Finely chop the leeks and mushrooms. Fry the leeks and mushrooms with the remaining oil from the tofu in the pan. Mix the vegetable juice, cornstarch and soy sauce. Add the tofu and let it simmer. Add salt and black pepper. Mushroom and Leek Tofu is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Avocado Zucchini Pasta recipe; Cut the squash into thin spaghetti. Saute it lightly in a pan without oil. Take the avocado, basil, salt and pepper from the blender until they get a creamy consistency. Mix the zucchini with the sauce and add sesame seeds. Zucchini Pasta with Avocado is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Walnut Carrot Porridge recipe; peel the carrot and pass it through the rondo. Mix almond milk, sweetener, cinnamon and nutmeg and let it boil. Continue cooking by adding the carrot and oat paste. When it thickens, add walnuts and coconuts when removed from the stove. Carrot Porridge with Walnut is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Pistachio and Carrot Noodle Salad recipe; boil the noodles. Roast the peanuts. Finely chop the spring onions and carrots and add them to the noodles. Mix soy sauce, maple syrup, coconut oil and lemon in a separate bowl and add to the noodles. Add sesame, fresh mint, coriander and roasted peanuts. Pistachio and Carrot Noodle Salad is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For Vegan Lentil Soup recipe; Add the lentils to the boiling vegetable broth. Wash and chop the carrots and leeks. Finely chop the onions and fry them in the pan. Add to boiling vegetable broth and lentils. Add salt and pepper. Vegan Lentil Soup is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For Vegan Mushroom Quinoa Risotto recipe; Wash the quinoa. Chop the garlic, onion and mushrooms. Saute lightly in olive oil. Add the quinoa and fry it. When the color changes slightly, add water and vegetable broth. Bake for 15-20 minutes. Add salt, pepper and spring onions close to cooking. Vegan Mushroom Quinoa Risotto is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For Vegan Blueberry Quinoa Porridge recipe; Cook the quinoa with 500 ml of water. After cooking, mix almond milk, blueberry, almond, vanilla and cinnamon and combine with quinoa. Vegan Blueberry Quinoa Porridge is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For Vegan Spinach Pizza recipe; Knead with wheat flour, dry yeast, water, olive oil. Dough 30 min. let it rest. Saute the onions and garlic and add the spinach and continue cooking. Puree the tomatoes in a separate place and add salt, thyme and black pepper. Unroll the fermented dough with your hands and place it on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. Add tomato sauce, cherry tomatoes and spinach mixture on it. Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated oven at 200 degrees. Vegan Spinach Pizza is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Vegan Avocado Sauce Potato recipe; In a bowl, mix water, curry, thyme, paprika, ground garlic, salt and pepper. Cut the potatoes into slices and mix with the spice mix. Bake at 200 degrees for 45 minutes. Mash the avocado with a fork and add lemon juice. Add the finely chopped tomatoes to the avocado mixture. Mash with a fork. Add thyme, salt and pepper. Put it as a sauce next to the potatoes that you have taken out of the oven. Potato with Vegan Avocado Sauce is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Vegan Peach Puree Sweet Couscous recipe, boil the coconut milk and add the couscous. After it cools down a bit and the couscous swells, add the mashed and sweetened peaches on it and mix. Vegan Sweet Couscous with Peach Puree is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Vegan Potato and Arugula Soup recipe; Boil the potatoes in salted water. Saute the garlic and onions in olive oil. Add the potatoes and add the vegetable broth. Finally, add the arugula and pass it through the blender. Add salt and pepper. Vegan Potato and Arugula Soup is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Vegan Ratatouille recipe; Saute the onions and garlic in olive oil. Chop 4 tomatoes into cubes and add to the pan with balsamic vinegar. Chop the zucchini, eggplant and remaining tomatoes into rounds. Add the tomato sauce first and then the ring vegetables to the baking tray. Bake at 180 degrees for 30-35 minutes. Squeeze the lemon juice when you take it out of the oven. Vegan Ratatouille is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the recipe for Vegan Baked Zucchini Slices with Tomatoes; Slice the zucchini into rounds. Prepare a mixture of salt, pepper, olive oil and lemon juice on it and apply it. Bake at 180 degrees for 10-15 minutes. When it comes out of the oven, garnish with slices of tomato on top. Vegan Baked Zucchini Slices with Tomatoes are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For Vegan Vegetable Stuffed Mushrooms recipe; Finely chop the zucchini, shallots, garlic and tomatoes and sauté in olive oil. Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and any other seasonings of your choice. Wash, peel and remove the stems of the mushrooms. Stuff the sautéed vegetables into the mushrooms. Bake in a preheated 200 degree oven for 10 minutes. Vegan Vegetable Stuffed Mushrooms are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

For the Vegan Mushroom Filled Potato Cake recipe; Boil the potatoes and mash them. Chop the onions and mushrooms and sauté lightly in olive oil. Add chopped parsley, salt and black pepper. Add flour to the cooled mashed potatoes. Take a spoonful of the flour puree mixture and place it on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. After putting the mushroom mixture on top, add another layer of mashed potatoes. Bake at 200 degrees for 30-35 minutes. Vegan Mushroom Stuffed Potato Cake is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For Vegan Curry and Coconut Chickpea Rice recipe; First of all, prepare the rice. Finely chop the onion and garlic and sauté them in coconut oil. Add the tomato and coconut milk and let it cook. Add all the spices and boiled chickpeas. Cook for another 15 minutes. Serve over the rice. Vegan Curry and Coconut Chickpea Rice is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Oatlı Fit Cookie recipe; First of all, chop the apricots into small pieces and pass them through the rondo. Then add walnuts, eggs, oat, baking soda and butter and continue to roll it. Wet your hands so that they do not stick, and take small pieces from the mixture and roll them. When you have finished the whole mixture, place them on a baking tray with greaseproof paper and bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 12-15 minutes. After it comes out of the oven, you can sprinkle cinnamon on it if you wish. Oatlı Fit Cookie is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal. :)

Add the crushed walnuts and vanilla into the peeled and grated red apple and cook it in the pan on medium heat. Eggs, whole wheat flour, lemon zest and olive oil are whisked and cooked in a medium-sized pan with a flat surface. We pour the apple mortar in the middle of the pancake we made and after wrapping it in the form of a roll, we cut it into 5-6 slices. Drizzle some honey on top and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.

After frying the spinach a little in 1 teaspoon of olive oil, we add the cottage cheese, a little salt and other spices. After whisking the eggs, oat flour, milk, lemon zest and a little salt, we pour 1 teaspoon of olive oil in the pan and pour the mixture. After the crepe is cooked, we put our spinach mixture between it and fold it in half and grate the mozzarella cheese on it and cook it in the oven for 3-4 minutes.

Fry the onion and spinach in 1 tablespoon of olive oil. In a separate pan, fry the oat flour in 1 tablespoon of olive oil and cook it by slowly adding milk. We mix the cheeses with the egg yolks. Beat the egg whites in a separate bowl, add them to the cheese mixture and mix. We add the other mixtures, salt and pepper to the fried onions and spinach and mix. We distribute it to the silicone oven cups that we grease and bake for 30-40 minutes at 180 degrees.

For the Broccoli Mucver recipe; Squeeze the zucchini with your hands to remove excess water or place them in a clean tea strainer and apply pressure. Then beat the eggs in a bowl. Then add the broccoli, zucchini and dill to the beaten eggs and mix well. Slowly add the flour and do not forget to mix while adding. When the mixing process is finished, add the spices you want. Heat the oil in a non-stick pan. Take the mixture piece by piece with a large serving spoon and pour it into the pan. Let it sit on medium heat for 3-4 minutes until one side turns brown, then turn and cook the other side. You won't need to add more oil to the pan after the first time. You can cook the remaining oil and the remaining ingredients in the pan with the help of a serving spoon. When all the muttons are ready, sprinkle the remaining dill over the muttons. Broccoli mucver is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Egg Mushroom recipe with Fried Tomatoes; Brush the mushrooms with a small amount of oil and garlic. Then place on a very lightly greased baking tray and sprinkle with a small amount of your desired seasonings. Garnish with chopped fresh thyme sprigs, cover with foil and bake in the oven preheated to 180 degrees for 20 minutes. After cooking, remove the foil, place the tomatoes next to the baked mushrooms and crack an egg on each of the mushrooms. At this stage, you can add a little more thyme if you want. Cook in this way for another 10-12 minutes. Take it out of the oven and serve with arugula if you wish. Fried Tomatoes and Egg Mushrooms are ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

For the Fried Tomato Green Omelet recipe: Heat the oil in a small non-stick skillet. Cook the tomatoes in this pan until they begin to soften and color. Meanwhile, whisk the eggs in a small bowl with the herbs and freshly ground black pepper. Then remove the tomatoes from the pan and place them on two separate serving plates. Pour the egg mixture into the pan and mix gently with a wooden spoon. Stop stirring close to cooking to allow it to become an omelet. Take the omelets from the pan, cut them into quarters and serve with the tomatoes. Green Omelet with Fried Tomatoes is ready to be served. Enjoy your meal.

For the Creamy Mushroom Open Top Toast recipe; Toast the bread without oil and then spread some cheese on it. Meanwhile, heat the oil in another non-stick pan and add the mushrooms and cook, stirring, until they soften. Mix the remaining cheese and mustard together with the milk in a bowl. Spread this mixture on toasted bread. Top with chives and mushrooms. Open Top Toast with Creamy Mushrooms is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal.

1- In a large saucepan, boil the water in which you have added a pinch of water. Add the pasta and cook until it boils. 2-While the pasta is boiling, add 3 tablespoons of olive oil, vinegar and a little black pepper to a small bowl. Whisk the ingredients and set aside. 3- Drain the cooked pasta and keep it aside. 4-Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large deep sauté pan over medium heat, add the broccoli you cut into pieces of the desired size and cook for about 4-5 minutes. 5-Add the broccoli to the strained pasta and mix. 6- First, add small pieces of white cheese, then olives to the pasta and mix lightly. Sprinkle with some salt and pepper, if desired.

1-Place the salmon in a bowl and mash until it breaks into tiny pieces. 2-Mix the ingredients except sandwich breads and barbecue sauce in another bowl. Then add the salmon and continue mixing with the help of a spoon until the ingredients are completely blended. 3-Divide the mixture you have obtained into 4 equal parts and give each part the shape of a burger patty. 4-Then heat a skillet or grill over medium-high heat and place the burger patties and cook for about four minutes until both sides are evenly browned. 5-After cooking, place the meatballs between sandwich breads made of whole grain, wholemeal or wheat flour, and serve with barbecue sauce, mustard, red onion and, if you wish, lettuce.

1- In a large and shallow bowl, mash the banana with a fork and mash it. 2-Add almond milk, flaxseed flour and cinnamon to the banana puree and mix. If you want to thin the resulting dough, add a little more almond milk. The important point about the consistency here is that the dough is ready to be poured. You can also add vanilla at this stage if you wish. 3- Let your dough rest for 5 minutes while preheating in a grill or pan over medium heat. 4-When the surface is warm, add vegan butter or coconut oil and drizzle a little. 5-Dip your bread slices into the liquid dough that you have rested for 5 minutes and press it with your finger so that it stays in the mixture for 5-10 seconds. 6-As soon as you take it out of the mixture, immediately transfer it to the pan or grill where you will cook. 7- Cook the slices of bread until they are evenly browned, holding both sides for 3-4 minutes. Be careful to turn it over carefully using a soft spatula because the banana mix can get sticky if you're not gentle. If the slices of bread turn brown too quickly, turn the heat down a little. 8-Finally, serve your toast by adding flavoring ingredients such as peanut butter and maple syrup to your liking.

1-Set the oven to 175 degrees. 2- Mix flour, oat, cinnamon, baking powder, sea salt and coconut. 3-In a separate bowl, mix the pumpkin puree, coconut sugar, coconut oil, flaxseed and vanilla. 4-Combine the two mixtures you have prepared. 5-Add the vegan dark chocolate pieces to this mixture and mix well again. 6- Take small balls from the resulting mixture with the help of a spoon and place them on the baking paper. Give the shape of cookies by pressing the balls with the help of a spoon or with your fingers. 7-Bake in the oven for 15-16 minutes. Don't forget to wait for the cookies to cool completely before transferring them to a storage container to eat later.

1- Mix the cooked quinoa, vegan mayonnaise, rice vinegar, hot sauce and green onion well in a mixing bowl. Drizzle some soy sauce on it. 2-Divide the quinoa mixture, greens, avocados and carrots into the lavash. Roll each lavash to form a burrito. Then divide it in half.

1- Melt the chocolate chips in a bain-marie over very low heat. 2- Using a small brush, coat the bottom and sides of the bar molds with chocolate. 3- Leave the bar molds in the freezer for 10 minutes to harden the chocolates you apply. 4-In a small bowl, combine chopped coconuts with coconut oil and honey. 5-Remove the bar molds from the freezer and fill these containers with the coconut mixture. 6- Paint the top of the mixture with melted chocolate with the help of a brush. 7- Leave the bar molds in the freezer for 10 minutes to harden. 8-Remove from the freezer, invert the molds and remove the bars from the molds.

1- Combine the dry ingredients and mix well. 2-Add the liquid ingredients into the mixture and mix, and then transfer the mixture to a bowl. 3-Bake in the microwave for 30-40 seconds or for about 14 minutes in an oven set to 175 degrees.

1-Boil the quinoa and let it cool. 2-Set your oven to 175 °C. 3-Mix the boiled quinoa with all the remaining ingredients. 4- After pouring the resulting mixture into a greased small muffin tray, bake for 15-18 minutes. 5- Wait for the quinoa balls to cool completely before removing them from the pan and do not use a knife. Once the quinoa balls are completely cooled, you can store them in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to 1 week. If you want to freeze it, you can transfer it to small plastic bags after it has cooled completely and store it in your freezer for up to 1 month.

1-Divide the English muffins in half and place them on the baking tray. 2- After applying 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce to each, sprinkle 1-1.5 tablespoons of grated cheese on them. 3-Place the vegetables and basil on the cheeses. 4-Bake for 2-4 minutes until the cheese melts and the edges of the muffins are crispy. You can store these practical muffin-pizzas in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to four days. After taking it out of the refrigerator, you can warm it in the oven and serve.

1-Preset the oven to 120 °C and cover one or two baking trays with baking paper, depending on the size. 2-Slice the apples with the help of a spiral chopper and put them in a bowl. 3-In a small bowl, mix the sugar and cinnamon. 4-Sprinkle the mixture on the apple slices and mix gently by throwing it into the bowl. 5-Place the slices in a single layer on the baking tray, leaving some space between them. 6- Bake for an hour and then turn each apple slice over. When you notice that the edges of the apple slices are starting to curl, you can do the flipping. After turning it, cook for another hour and then turn off the oven. Leave in the oven until the apple chips have cooled. This will turn them into chips. You can store your apple chips in an airtight container for several days.

1-Put the coconut flakes in a small pan on the stove. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until lightly browned. Allow to cool before mixing with other ingredients. 2- Transfer the toasted coconut flakes and all remaining ingredients to a large bowl or storage container and mix well. 3- Store the mixture in an airtight container at room temperature or divide it for disposable use and put it in zip-top bags.

1- Melt the coconut oil in a large bowl. 2-Add almond oil and honey and mix until soft. Then add the oat, chia seeds, flax seeds and then all the remaining ingredients and mix well. 3- Take an amount of 1 tablespoon of the resulting mixture, roll it until the material is gone and give it a ball shape.

1- Cook the grated carrots with 3 tablespoons of olive oil until soft, then remove from the stove and leave to cool. 2-Strained yoghurt, salt and crushed garlic are whisked together. 3-Cooled carrots are mixed into the whipped yogurt. 4-Then it is kept in the refrigerator until serving.

1-Take off the stems of the mushrooms, keep them in cold water with vinegar to clean them thoroughly. 2-The cleaned mushrooms are taken out of the water and placed on a towel. 3-Chop the mushrooms in a small size. 4- Put olive oil in the pan, add the mushrooms when it gets hot. Salt is added to it and left to cook on medium heat. 5-The mushrooms are mixed when the color of one side changes and butter is added to it. 6- Sauteing is continued and grated garlic is added on it. 7- It is cooked slowly in about 10 minutes and black pepper is added on it while serving.

1. Onions are chopped for cooking, fried in 4 tablespoons of oil in the pot. 2. Carrots and potatoes are cut into cubes. 3, When the onion is roasted, tomato paste is added and mixed for a few minutes. 4. Add potatoes, carrots and peas to the pot. Add salt and pepper and mix for a few more minutes. 5. Hot water is added to the pot and the food is cooked for 40 minutes on low heat.

1-Set the oven to 200 °C. 2- Spread the chickpeas that you have kept in water overnight on a cutting board on which you have paper towels. Gently rub with another towel until dry and let it dry for another 10 minutes. 3-Add the chickpeas to a large bowl poured 1 tablespoon of olive oil and mix. 4-Place the chickpeas on a baking tray covered with baking paper and bake for 30 minutes. 5- After shaking the baking tray and ensuring that the chickpeas are turned inside out, cook for another 15 minutes. 6-Meanwhile, mix brown sugar, cayenne pepper powder, cumin, black pepper and salt in a large bowl with the remaining 1 teaspoon of olive oil. 7- Pour this mixture over the roasted chickpeas in the oven. 8-Bake the chickpeas for another 5-10 minutes so that they are crispy and crispy.

1- Mix the eggs, Italian seasoning and salt. Then add the quinoa, breadcrumbs, parmesan, spinach, garlic, onion and sun-dried tomatoes. 2-Heat the olive oil in a large pan. 3-Cut your quinoa mixture into 15 meatballs and fry both sides for 2-3 minutes.

1-Set the oven to 175 °C. 2- Smooth the lentils you have boiled until soft with the help of a fork or a food processor. 3-In a large bowl, mix eggs, applesauce, vanilla, yogurt and brown sugar. 4-In a separate bowl, mix the flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda. 5-Combine these two separate mixtures and continue mixing until you get a homogeneous consistency. 6- Pour the mixture into the cake molds. Sprinkle coconut on them. Bake for 7-20-25 minutes, until a toothpick comes out completely without dough.

1-Preset the oven to 200 °C. Lightly grease the inside of a 2-12 cake tin pan. 3-Divide each tortilla bread into 3-4 pieces and place them in the molds. 4- Spread a teaspoon of homemade tomato sauce in the middle of each. 5-Sprinkle cheese on them and then add the bacon pieces and bake for 10-12 minutes. 6- Wait for the mini pizzas to cool before transferring them from the cake mold to the serving plate. 7-Finally, decorate your pizza with chopped parsley.

1-Peel the thin layer on the outer surface of the broccoli stems. 2-Put the stems in a bowl and steam them lightly. 3-Add all ingredients except olive oil to a food processor and mix until homogeneous. 4-When you get a perfect creamy mixture, add 1 tablespoon of oil into it. At this stage, if the mixture is too dense, you can add as much water as necessary.

1 - Pre-heat the oven to 190 degrees. 2 - Peel off the tough outer layer of broccoli stems and slice into french fries. 3 - Place the broccoli stalks on a baking tray lined with baking paper. 4 - In another bowl, mix the oil, salt, pepper and garlic. Then apply this mixture on the stems you placed on the tray. 5 - Bake for 25 - 30 minutes until the stems are lightly browned.

Mix egg, coconut oil and vanilla until foamy. Bananas and dates are mashed with a fork. Add cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon, carob extract to the mixture and mix. Add 1 glass of oat to the last mixture. It is arranged with the help of a spoon on a tray lined with greaseproof paper. It is cooked in a controlled oven at 180 degrees.

After mixing the dough, wrap it with a damp towel for half an hour and wait. It is baked for half an hour in the oven at 190 degrees. In addition to the ingredients, there is half a glass of lentil flour. 1 glass of water should be warm.

Stir the butter and chocolate over low heat until melted. After it melts, take it off the stove. Add rice flour to it and mix well. In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs and sugar until foamy. Then add the chocolate and continue mixing. Pour into the greased souffle cups half full. Bake in a preheated 220 degree oven for 7 minutes. Dark chocolate must be gluten-free.

First of all, we pass the cauliflowers that we wash through the robot. We mix the ingredients for the base, make it ready, spread it on the tray and bake in the oven for 10 minutes. Pour the sauce on it and decorate it with whatever you want. Finally, we bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 25-30 minutes. You should make sure that the cracker is gluten-free. You can use corn, roasted cheddar, cheddar cheese and olives as a topping.

Preset your oven to 180 degrees. Spread oatmeal, walnuts, quinoa and chia seeds on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Cut the greaseproof baking paper according to the dimensions of the baking tray you will use. In a small saucepan, melt the peanut butter a little, add the honey and let the mixture become smooth. Then add vanilla, cinnamon and salt into the mixture. Then, pour the oat and chia seed mixture into a large mixing bowl, add the peanut butter mixture on top and mix well, slowly add the dried fruits. Transfer the resulting mixture to the baking dish on which you have greased paper and make sure that it is evenly distributed. Refrigerate for about 2 hours until your bars are ready, slice and serve.

Heat the oil in a medium skillet over low heat and add the onions and sauté until soft. Then add the garlic and continue this process until you can smell the smell. Bring the vegetable broth, spinach, salt, pepper, chia seeds and rosemary to a boil over high heat. After boiling, reduce the heat a little and continue cooking with the lid open, stirring occasionally, until the spinach wilts. Then add the beans and stir until the beans are fully heated. Finally, add the parsley and any spices you like. Here is your dinner ready!

All the ingredients are kneaded, then covered and left to ferment for an hour. * Then it is shaped and placed on the tray. * It is kept here for 20 minutes and it is ensured that it swells well. * You can decorate the top as you wish. * We bake in the oven at 80 degrees for 45 minutes. Enjoy your meal..

First, heat the milk on low heat. Add sugar and dry yeast, mix and leave for about 10 minutes. After adding the oil, salt and flour, leave it for another 20 minutes. Set your oven to 180 degrees. Divide the dough into 4 equal parts. After opening the pieces with the help of a roller, spread the chocolate hazelnut cream inside. Shape and place on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. After the dough is finished, brush the egg yolk on it and put it in the oven. Cook until browned.

Wheat flour, corn starch, sugar, vanilla, milk and egg yolk whisk well and cook over medium heat. When it reaches the consistency of custard, remove it from the stove. When it cools down, add the cream and whisk until you get a smooth consistency. Pulse the oatli biscuits with the robot until they become flour. Add 2 spoons of the biscuits you have turned into flour to the serving bowls. Slice the strawberries and place half of them on the biscuits. Then add some cream on it and 2 more spoons of biscuits on top of the cream. After adding the remaining cream and strawberries, your magnolia is ready to serve. Enjoy your meal :)
Roasted peppers and roasted eggplants are chopped and added to boiled beans. Olive oil is added and mixed. Dry dill is added on it. ENJOY....
We cook all the ingredients in the pan. Chop the strawberries on it. Bon appetit...

First of all, if the oat is not in flour form, it is rolled with the help of a rondo. 2 pieces of banana, tahini, date and oat flour are kneaded by hand and turned into dough. Spread the tart dough into the baking mold. It is placed in the mold by giving shape with the help of hand. (You can wet your hands with water so that the dough does not stick to your hands) Cut the remaining 2 bananas thinly and lengthwise and bake in the oven at 180 C for 20 minutes. Enjoy your meal…

The fruits are crushed well, all the ingredients are mixed and baked in the oven at 180 C. NOTE: Amma velakin; Even if we say there is no flour, we use carob powder, and even if we say no sugar, we sweeten it with dates/bananas/molasses. Enjoy your meal…

Washed pearls are soaked in boiling water for 15-20 minutes. The stem on the head is cut off and the inside of it is opened with the help of fingers, chopped walnuts and cinnamon are mixed and the pearls are filled. Honey is poured evenly over the figs taken into the pot, 2-3 tablespoons of hot water is poured into the bottom of the pot and cooked for 15-20 minutes, with the lid closed, on the lowest heat. You can decorate it with walnuts. Enjoy your meal...

Figs are soaked in hot water for 15-20 minutes. Soft figs are chopped. The milk is taken from the stove before it boils completely. Fig and milk are passed through a blender. It is filled into bowls and yoghurt is covered and rested in the dark for 3-3.5 hours like yeast. It can be decorated with whole walnuts. Enjoy your meal...

First, let's separate the egg whites from the yolks and beat the whites until they become foamy. In a bowl, add the egg yolk, vanilla, milk and mashed banana with a fork. Let's mix it with a blender. Then add the oat flour and continue mixing with the blender. Let's add the egg white last and continue mixing with the help of a spoon without a blender. Let's pour enough oil to wet the pan, pour it into the pan in the size of a spoon, and cook it on both sides in the pan. NOTE: If your banana is not ripe, it will be more sugar-free. You can also make 2 bananas. If you want it to be sweeter; You can also add 1 tablespoon of DATE EXTRACT or CAROB. The choice is yours :) Bon appetit...

Divide 4 artichokes into 4. Chop the peas, carrots, onions and add them to a large saucepan. Add 1 squeezed orange. Add 3-4 tablespoons of olive oil. Pour hot water up to the top of all materials. We cook for 20 -25 minutes. If you are going to use ready-made side dishes, you should wash the garnishes and add the artichoke 10 minutes after cooking. And of course, let's not forget to add a little salt. Enjoy your meal..

Chopped onions, sweet potatoes, carrots and zucchini are cooked in olive oil. Then the meat is added and cooked a little more. Boiled water is added to it, rice noodles are added, and it is continued to cook on low heat until it absorbs its water. Seasonings are added last. I deliberately didn't add the salt. The ingredients already contain enough salt. Enjoy your meal...

Beat eggs, salt and sugar in a bowl. Add all the ingredients except egg yolk, sesame and black cumin and knead all the ingredients well. After the dough is rested for 10 minutes, sticks of the desired length are made from the dough. Take it on a baking tray, brush with egg yolk, pour sesame seeds mixture on it. Bake in a preheated oven at 180 C for 15-20 minutes. Enjoy your meal...

Boil the rice with 2 tea glasses of water and salt until the water is gone. Add the almond milk to the pan. Boil together for 15 minutes on medium heat. Then we add the rice flour, but first mix it with 1 tablespoon of water in a small bowl, add 1 scoop of hot almond milk, add it to the pot slowly and it bleeds for another 15 minutes. Add the vanilla close to closing. Turn off the heat and let it cool for 10 minutes. When it cools down, add the honey and mix well for the last time. Enjoy your meal...
Boil the pumpkin in a little water and pass it through with the other ingredients. Then shape into walnut-sized rounds. Garnish it with cocoa, coconut or flax seeds. Enjoy your meal.

Dissolve the yeast in warm water. On the other hand, mix the flour and salt. Make a hole in the middle of the flour and add the yeast water and olive oil on it. Knead until you get a smooth, homogeneous consistency. Ferment the dough for 30 minutes. Shape into long strips and brush with egg yolk. Finally, sprinkle sesame seeds and bake in the oven at 170 degrees for 15-20 minutes. Enjoy your meal.

All the ingredients will be chopped in appropriate sizes and mixed in a large bowl. Olive oil will be added to it. There will be no need for vinegar and lemon, as the salad has a sour taste due to the fruits.
The egg is boiled. 1 potato is boiled. Cut potatoes and eggs. All ingredients are mixed. Drizzle olive oil on it and optionally add a pinch of salt.
Potatoes are boiled and chopped. The parsley is finely chopped. Fresh onion is chopped. All the ingredients are mixed. Add sumac and salt to it. Olive oil is poured.
Bulgur is boiled. Mint, parsley and dill are finely chopped. Green onions are chopped. Walnuts crumble. All ingredients are mixed and oil is added.
We cook mushrooms and asparagus in a non-stick pan or in a toaster. Lettuce is chopped, roasted peppers are chopped. All ingredients are mixed. Drizzle with olive oil and add a pinch of salt. Served.
Cauliflower is boiled. Chop green onions and parsley. All ingredients are mixed. Add pomegranate syrup, lemon sauce and olive oil on it. Served.
Broccoli is boiled. It is served with olive oil, lemon and garlic mixture on it.

Add oat paste, curd cheese and curd in a bowl. Eggs are added to it. Finely chopped dill and parsley are added to the mixture. All the ingredients are mixed in a bowl and shaped with the help of a spoon and placed on the tray. Baked in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 17-20 minutes.

Mash the banana into a puree with a fork. Then whisk all the ingredients well. Grease the pan with the help of a napkin. After it gets hot, transfer the dough you prepared with the help of a ladle to the pan. When the dough rises and eye to eye, turn the other side and cook.

Boil the chopped broccoli, carrots and zucchini in water. Cook for about 20 minutes until the vegetables are soft. After boiling, add milk and oil. Take it from the stove and add salt and pepper, then blend it. Then take it back to the stove and boil for another 1-2 minutes.

Brew 1 teaspoon of coffee in half a glass of water. Mix oat paste, coffee and milk in a bowl. After warming up, add labneh and honey and mix. Leave to cool in the refrigerator. Add cocoa and banana on top. Enjoy your meal!

Roast the red peppers on an open fire. Peel and chop the skins. Saute with olive oil and add the grated garlic. Add the chili paste. After 5-6 minutes, add 1 tablespoon of flour. After the flour is cooked, add hot water and cook until the peppers soften. Pass the soup through a blender and season with salt and pepper.

Bake the pumpkin at 200 degrees until it softens. Saute the onion, potato and carrot slices in oil. After adding the pumpkin to the mixture, cook it with enough water to cover it for 15-20 minutes. After adding the milk, boil it again.

The meat is chopped as smaller than the cubed. Dry onions, carrots, potatoes are washed and cut into small cubes. If the peas are fresh, they are sorted and washed. If taken from the freezer, it is only washed. The pot is put on fire and heated well. Meat is added and it is kept on the hot surface for 2-3 minutes, allowing it to absorb the water. Add a few drops of oil and fry it. Add 2 tablespoons of oil and chopped onion and fry it. Add tomato paste, carrots and peas and mix. Add 3 cups of hot water and let it cook on medium heat. When the carrots are cooked, potatoes, salt and half a cube of sugar are added and left to cook on low heat. When the peas are cooked, your meal is ready.

Wash and peel all vegetables thoroughly. Peel and finely chop or grate the onion and garlic in the same way. Put the vegetables in the pot and pour boiling water over them. When the vegetables are soft, pass them through the blender and serve hot.

Transfer chopped cabbage, carrot, onion, capia pepper, onion, garlic, and chili pepper to a large saucepan. Add enough water to cover it by 2 inches and let it boil over medium heat with the lid closed. After boiling, lower the stove. Add lemon juice, black pepper, cumin and turmeric into the soup and cook for 5 more minutes on low heat. Finally, add the chopped parsley and dill, mix and remove from the stove.

PASS the oat THROUGH THE ROBOT, ADD VANILLINE, BAKING POWDER, HAZELNUT, FIG, HONEY, COCOA, EGG, MILK AND MIX IT WELL. BAKE FOR 40 MINUTES AT 180°C PRE-HEATED AFTER IT IS MOLDED. YOU CAN ADD RAW ALMOND AND WALNUT FOR DECORATION ON IT…

Chop Cabbage Finely and Boil in Boiled Water for 15 Minutes, then filter, add grated potatoes, grated carrots, chopped parsley, canned tomatoes and mashed corn. AFTER COOKING IT WELL, THE ONIONS ARE CHOPPED IN A FRONT PAN, Chop Into Cubes, AND FINISHED WITH A LITTLE OIL AND A LITTLE PASSAGE, AFTER IT IS ADDED TO THE MIXTURE AND HOW WATER IS REQUESTED, ADD A LOT OF SALT WITH ADDITIONAL SALT.

The inside of the pumpkin seeds are removed. The oats are pulled from the blender in a way that is not thin. Take it in a bowl (2 times is enough) and add butter, egg, vanilla, pumpkin seed kernels, raisins and honey into it, mix well. Blueberries can be used instead of raisins. Rest in the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes. It is rolled out with the help of a spoon and placed on greaseproof paper, baked at 180 degrees for 15-20 minutes (take it out of the oven when it is browned).

WE KEEP THE ONION, GARLIC, AND PEPPER GREAT SMALL GRIND AND COOK IT TOGETHER WITH OIL, AFTER ROASTING, WE ADD CUBE CHOPPED TOMATOES AND SPICES ON IT, AND AFTER SOUPING THE WATER, WE LEFT THE WATER, AFTER SOUPING THE WATER. WE LEAVE THE WASHED CHICKEN IN THE POT TO SAUT IT, IF IT COOKES ON LOW FIRE WITH ITS OWN JUICE IT WILL BE DELICIOUS! WE COMBINE IT WITH PASTA AND MIX IT WELL.

EGGS, SALT AND SUGAR ARE WHILE WHILE WHICH ARE WHILE IN A CONTAINER, ALL THE INGREDIENTS EXCEPT EGG YOLK, SESAME NIPPLE IS ADDED TO IT AND IT IS WELL Kneaded. THE Dough IS RESTED FOR 5-10 MINUTES. ON THE OVEN AFTER IT HAS BEEN PLACED ON THE OVEN TRAY Spread the egg yolk and add sesame and black seed if desired. COOK FOR 15.-20 MINUTES IN A PRE-HEATED OVEN.

Mix 1 EGG, 2 Tablespoons Rye Flour/Whole Wheat Flour/Chickpea Flour ETC., 3 Tablespoons Milk, 1 Tablespoon flaxseed. THE PAN IS WETTED WITH 1 TASSES OF OLIVE OIL AND THE BAVASH IS PREPARED BY COOKING WITH REVERSE FRONT. WE PUT OTHER INGREDIENTS THROUGH RONDO. AFTER WORKING, +1 BOILED Sliced EGG CAN BE ADDED IF YOU WANT.

Add all the ingredients one by one, mix and knead the dough. We add gluten-free flour as much as it takes, we can stop adding flour when the consistency of the dough reaches the consistency of earlobes. We take a walnut-sized piece from the dough and roll it in our palms and put cheese the size of hazelnuts in it and give it a round shape. Brushed with egg yolk and optionally sprinkled with black cumin or sesame seeds. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

1 EGG, 2 Tablespoons Rye Flour/Whole Wheat Flour/Chickpea Flour ETC., 3 Tablespoons Milk 1 Tablespoon of flaxseed, 1 Tablespoon of OLIVE OIL (THROUGH BLEACHING BREAKED WASH TO WEET THE AIR, BREED BREED BREAKFAST) WE ARE RIPPING. SAUT THE MUSHROOM. MIX THE REMAINING INGREDIENTS AND THE MUSHROOM FINELY IN A BOWL, ADD MORTAR TO THE COOKED lavaSH.

FOR THE BASE, oat, hazelnut, 2 medium bananas are passed through a blender. (If it is solid, a little coconut oil can be added) The mixture is taken into the container where the cooking will be done and left to cool after 10 minutes in a preheated 180° oven. MIDDLE PART ; 6-7 tablespoons of labneh, 3-4 ripe bananas, 1 egg, 2 tablespoons of peanut butter, 1 pinch of salt, 2 pinches of vanilla are whisked and the consistency is created. All the material is poured over the previously prepared and cooled sub-base material and cooked at 150 degrees for 30 minutes. (After cooking, it is cooled down again and brought to room temperature.) 2 medium-sized ripe persimmons, 2 tablespoons of peanut butter, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, 1 tablespoon of carob flour, 1 teaspoon of honey. Pour over the previously prepared cooked and cooled material. It is kept in the refrigerator for 1 night.

Chop the strawberries and put them in a deep pan. Add brown sugar and water and boil them. When the strawberries soften slightly, puree them with the help of a blender and leave to cool. Cut the vanilla stick in half and mix the vanilla grains into the yogurt. Fill your cups or glasses first with strawberry sauce, then with yogurt, and by putting chocolate chips and hazelnut pieces in the middle layer. 2-3 bowls come out of the recipe. 1 cup (medium) 254 kcal

Let's take our low-fat ground beef into the kneading bowl. Put salt, spices and baking soda in it and knead. Grate the onion and squeeze out the juice. Add the garlic and onion to the ground beef spice mix. Let's knead well. You can adjust the size of the spices yourself. Let it sit in the refrigerator for at least half an hour. Bake in the oven at 200 degrees for 30 minutes by laying oiled paper. There are 17 pieces in total from the recipe. 1 piece is 60 kcal

In a bowl, whisk together the molasses, oil and egg. Then add the baking powder and flour, mix to prepare the cookie dough. Place the cookie on the tray you have covered with greaseproof paper. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for about 20 minutes. 10 slices of cookies come out. 1 slice is 85-90 kcal.

Boil your pasta in water and drain the water. Put the milk, butter and cheddar cheese in the pot, add the pasta. Cook, stirring, until the pasta absorbs the milk. Then add salt and pepper and remove from the stove. Makes 4 servings from the recipe. 1 serving is 387 calories

Boil your pasta in water and drain the water. Toss olive oil and chopped sausages in a pan. Lightly fry the sausages. Add tomato paste and grated tomatoes on it. Cook for about 5 minutes. Then transfer the sausage sauce over the drained pasta. Add the spices and salt and mix well. There are 4 portions from the recipe. 1 serving is 314 calories

Chickens are boiled and cut into small pieces. Cucumbers are peeled and chopped into small pieces. Dill is chopped. Mayonnaise, crushed garlic and yogurt are mixed in a separate bowl and all ingredients are combined. Coarsely crushed walnuts and salt are added and taken into the serving bowl. 1 plate is about 240 kcal

Divide the cherry tomatoes from which you removed the stems into four equal parts. Cut the pitted green olives into small cubes. Finely chop the parsley and dill. Take the boiled wheat, the water of which you have drained, into a deep salad bowl. Mix with the chopped salad ingredients. Mix olive oil and salt in a small bowl and add the dressing you prepared to the salad. Finally, add the finely ground walnuts and mix the salad. Take out 1 bowl from the recipe. 1 cup medium 220 kcal

Chop the onion. Chop the potatoes and carrots to the same size. Heat the olive oil in a saucepan. Fry the onions. Continue frying the potatoes and carrots together with the onions. Add salt and pepper, turmeric and mix. Then add water and let it boil. When the carrots and potatoes are soft, blend the soup with a hand blender until it reaches a smooth consistency. Let it boil for another 5-6 minutes. 1 bowl 113 calories
Leek and carrot are sautéed and eggs are whisked and omelette is cooked

We mix all the ingredients except the peppers in a bowl and cook them in a fireproof pan until the chicken turns color. After the chickens turn color, we add our red and green peppers and cook until the water is absorbed. We take our ready sauté on a serving plate and serve it hot. Enjoy your meal !

Mix tomato paste, spices and olive oil in a bowl. Then add the chicken, potatoes and carrots in order and mix them well into the sauce. Arrange the ingredients on the greaseproof paper lined tray. After adding a large glass of water to it, cover it with a greaseproof paper and pinch the edges. Bake in the oven at 200 degrees for 45 minutes.

Soak your rice in boiled water to release its starch. Then drain the water and set aside. Take a flat pan on the stove and pour the olive oil. After it gets hot, add the turmeric and cumin to the oil and mix it lightly so that it combines with the oil. Add your rice and continue to stir fry. You can dim the stove. When the yellow-orange color of turmeric is evenly distributed over all the rice, add 1 cup of hot water to it. Mix it for the last time and bury the bay leaf well into the rice to give it flavor and let it cook on the lowest heat with the lid closed. After about 20 minutes, the Turmeric Rice is ready. Enjoy your meal !

After washing the spinach well, cut it thinly. Pour the olive oil into the heated pan and add the spinach and 1 tea glass of water. Fry for 1-2 minutes. Then add all the spices and add 1.5 cups of water and mix. Finally, add 1-2 thin slices of lemon and cook on low heat with the lid closed. Check every 5-6 minutes. After cooking, you can put it on a plate and garnish it with lemon slices and serve. Enjoy your meal !

1. Mash the banana with a fork. 2. Add egg and milk and mix well. 3. Then we add oat flour, baking powder and vanilla and whisk until homogeneous. 4. We pour it in the size we want in our very little oiled pan and cook it back and forth. You can consume it with any fruit you want by spreading sugar-free peanut butter on it!

1. For the chips sauce; Mix tomato paste, oil and spices. For the yogurt sauce; Mix yoghurt and spices. 2. We spread the tomato paste mixture we prepared on the front and back sides of the lavash. 3. We cut the lavash into lozenges. 4. Take a baking tray and bake at 180°C for 8-10 minutes in a controlled manner. 5. Take it out of the oven and serve it with yogurt sauce after it cools down. 1 small bowl

1. Wash the cauliflower, cut it into small pieces and boil it in a saucepan. 2. On the other hand, we add the spices we want and fry the minced meat in its own oil. 3. Take the boiled cauliflower on a plate and add our minced meat and yoghurt on it. 4. On a separate side, we make our tomato paste sauce and pour it over the yogurt and enjoy it!

1. First of all, we melt our oil. 2. Then we make our dough by adding flour, oil and water. 4. At that time, we slice our strawberries and add honey on it, waiting for the strawberries to release their juice. 5. We take the rested dough from the fridge and roll it in 3-4 pieces (you can also open it as one piece if you want.) 6. We put our strawberries in the middle of the dough and close them from the edges. 7. Finally, we rub the remaining juice of the strawberries on the edges of the dough. 8. We bake in a preheated 170°C oven for 15-20 minutes under control. 9. We take it out of the oven and enjoy it!

1. We chop the figs and pass them through the rondo. 2. Add the tahini and egg and pass it through the rondo again. 3. Add the flour and vanilla and mix well. 4. We cut our walnuts into small pieces and add them to our dough. 5. After mixing well, we break off small pieces and shape them. 6. Bake in a 180°C oven for 10-15 minutes in a controlled manner. Enjoy your meal!

Boil the broccoli for 10-15 minutes. Take the boiling broccoli to the robot and mash it. Add the onion to the robot and pull both of them in the robot. Add the egg and mix. Add the breadcrumbs slowly and knead. You can cook it by shaping it with your hands, or you can keep it in the freezer and consume it later.

All the ingredients except the chocolate drop are mixed and kneaded well, then the chocolate drops are added and straightened a little more. After the cookies of the desired size are obtained, they are baked in a 170' oven for 20-30 minutes. If you want it sweeter, you can add vanilla. Instead of molasses, you can use palm extract or honey.

Mix yeast with 1 cup of warm water. Sugar is also added. Then add milk, yogurt, oil and mix. Add 1 egg white. Then about 2-3 cups of flour is added gradually, salt is added and kneaded. Its consistency will be a little runny (this makes the pastry soft. Then it is rested and left for fermentation. (I then take it apart in pieces and leave it to ferment again for about 10 minutes... The pastries are made in the desired size, sliced olives are added, egg yolk is applied on them and black cumin is added to it.) It is baked for 30 minutes in a 180' degree oven. Bon appetit... Dietician Gülçin Işık takes the dough as it is added, it becomes a problem when it is gluten-free. However, if you touch olive oil on your hand, the dough does not stick!

Onions are cut into cubes and sautéed a little in oil, tomato paste is added, black pepper, red pepper are added. Add boiled potatoes and mix well. (Let it cool down) Eggs are whisked into a deep bowl, oil, yogurt, milk, a little salt are added. When the potatoes get cold, gluten-free gullaç phyllo dough is put one by one in a tray covered with greaseproof paper and soaked. Potatoes are added when half of the package is finished. the remaining half package is put in the same way, after all the gullaç phyllo dough is finished, the remaining mixture is poured into the tray and sliced, and rested for 20 minutes. Then, a mixture of black cumin and sesame seeds is added. It is baked in the oven at 170-180 degrees until it turns golden brown. ( 30 -40 minutes ) You can make gluten-free pastry with either cheese or minced meat.

All materials except oat and chocolate chips are passed through the blender. Then oat and chocolate chips are added. Additions are made on oiled paper with the help of a spoon (it can be in the desired size according to preference). Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for an average of 15 minutes until golden brown. Enjoy your meal. Dietitian Gülçin, our light needs to be mature. I used palm extract instead of honey, you can use whatever you want. The material may be a little runny. It doesn't stay runny after cooking.

Almond flour, tahini, date honey, all the ingredients are thoroughly mixed, shaped into walnut-sized balls, then covered with sesame. After it is placed on the baking tray, it is slightly flattened with the bottom of the glass. Bake in the oven at 170 degrees for 10 minutes until golden brown. Enjoy your meal. Dietitian Gülçin IşıkI used date palm honey. Care must be taken while baking in the oven. It can burn in an instant.

Beat the eggs with a mixer. Add other ingredients except walnuts and continue beating. Cut the walnuts into small pieces and add to the mixture and mix with a wooden/plastic spoon. Grease the cake mold with a napkin or oil brush and pour the mixture into the mold. Grease the cake mold with a napkin or oil brush and pour the mixture into the preheated mold. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 40 minutes. After cooking, let it cool down. After cooling, you can take it out of the mold and serve.
Mung beans are boiled. Other ingredients are added to the boiled beans by finely chopping them. Served with olive oil and lemon dressing.

Whisk the milk and egg yolk in a saucepan. Then put this mixture on the stove and cook it by adding cornstarch and cocoa in medium heat. After boiling, remove from the stove and add the stevia, mix well. Pour into bowls, leave in the fridge to cool.

Cut the lavash into triangular pieces. Mix the paste with water. Add spices as desired. Mix the lavash with the sauce you prepared. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 5-7 minutes until the tops are golden brown.
Brew the espresso in a glass and froth 1 sb of milk either with the help of a french press or with a milk frother. Then, first combine the coffee and then the milk you frothed in a cup.

First boil the carrot, onion and chicken in the same pot. After 15 minutes, add the zucchini and broccoli and continue to boil for a while. After the chicken and vegetables are completely boiled, add olive oil, salt and spices. Finally, add parsley and serve. Soup for 2 people contains 30 g of carbohydrates.

Boil 2 tablespoons of quinoa with 1 tbs of water. While the quinoa is boiling, grill 150 g of chicken in a pan without oil. Slice the lettuce, tomato and avocado and put them in the salad bowl. Add the boiled quinoa and the chicken cooked in the pan to the bowl, add oil and lemon. 1 plate of chicken quinoa salad contains 45 g of carbohydrates.

Whisk together the apple juice concentrate, milk, egg, and coconut oil. Add cocoa, oat flour and baking powder and continue beating. Grease my small square bore and pour the mixture into it. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 35 minutes. 1 slice contains 9 g of carbohydrates.

Blend all ingredients except chia in a food processor for 40-60 seconds. Then turn the processor to the lowest speed, discard the chia and blend for 1 more minute. If your food processor does not have low speed, eat the chia with a spoon. Pour it into an airtight container and put it in the refrigerator. It should wait at least 5 hours. You can decorate it after taking it out of the fridge. If you want chocolate, all you have to do is add ½ cup of cocoa to the food processor. You can add pomegranate to decorate it. 1 portion of pudding contains 110 kcal.
Let's boil the chickpeas and wheat Let's mix 2 glasses of water with yoghurt, salt and the spices we want Mix all the ingredients and sprinkle dill on it Can be served cold or hot

Chop the leeks and carrots in julienne. After arranging a row in the pan, slice the onions between them and continue arranging them. Lastly, add salt, black pepper, 1 tea glass of tangerine juice and 1/2 tea glass of lemon juice and continue cooking. After the carrots soften, your dish is ready. Enjoy your meal
Bananas are mashed with a fork. It is mixed with carob extract and egg. The ingredients are added sequentially. Add 1 whole banana and walnuts on it. It is cooked in the oven at 180 degrees.
Mung beans are boiled. Green onions, oranges and cherry tomatoes are cut into cubes. All the ingredients are mixed in a bowl.
Broccoli is steamed or boiled. Brussels sprouts and garlic are sautéed together.

Beat eggs and sugar until foamy. All ingredients are added except flour, then flour is added. Carrots and walnuts are added to the oven. It is cooked at 180 degrees, 1-2 cups of gluten-free flour can be added according to the consistency. However, you may need to add 2 cups of flour exactly like oat flour.

The mozzarella cheese is grated, the other ingredients are chopped into small sizes, all the ingredients are added, and mixed well. It is shaped and put on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper. The dough can be shaped with a slightly sticky spoon. Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

Mix the milk, egg yolk and rice flour and cook it on the stove until it boils. Vanillin close to boiling, honey is added. The biscuits are crumbled, first custard, then strawberries and biscuits are added to a glass or bowl. Then custard is added again and decorated as desired.

Take the ground beef in the mixing bowl. Combine with egg, grated onion, grated garlic, finely chopped parsley, salt, cumin, breadcrumbs and black pepper. Let the prepared meatball mixture rest in the refrigerator for 15-20 minutes. To prepare the sauce, tomato puree, sugar, salt, pepper, oil and tomato paste are used for 2 teas. Warm the glass in hot water. Add ketchup and garlic. Make some big meatballs from the meatballs. You will see that the meatballs shrink when cooked. Cut the hamburger buns in half. After dipping the bread in the sauce, put the meatballs in it. Cover the last bread with sauce. Put the hamburger plate in the pot with boiling water and close the lid. The hamburgers will soften in 1 to 2 minutes under the steam of the water. Enjoy your meal.

Thinly slice the turnips. Boil until soft in boiling salted water. Knead all the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl. Put the mortar in the middle of each turnip slice and fold it to form the letter 'D'. Fold all the turnips in the same way. Place a plate on top of the pan to create weight. Turn down the heat when it starts boiling. Let it cook for 25 minutes. Strain the excess water and let it rest for 10 minutes, then you can serve it. Bon appetit. Do not forget to spread the turnip slices at the bottom so that the bottom of the pot does not stick.

Mix the flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a bowl. After adding butter and water, start kneading. Cover the dough and leave it to ferment for 45 minutes. Tear off the dough and place the meringue in the greased baking dish. Brush with egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake in a preheated 200 degree oven for 15-20 minutes. Bon appetit.

First, set the oven to 200 degrees. Soak the rice in warm salted water for a while. Take the oil in the pan and add the vermicelli. Fry the noodle until it thickens. Continue frying after adding the rice. Take the Bordeaux mixture and pour 2 cups of boiling water. Melt the chicken bouillon in the mixture and cover it with another pyrex. Cook in the oven at 170 degrees with the lower setting open. Enjoy your meal. Before starting the recipe, make sure to soak the rice in water for 15 minutes. Make sure the oven is preheated.

Mix 1 glass of warm water, sugar and yeast and let it rest for 10 minutes. Add salt and olive oil to the mixture. In step 2, add the melted butter at room temperature along with the flour. After the dough reaches a non-sticky consistency, let it rest for 1 hour. Roast the sesame seeds in the pan and mix the molasses with half a glass of water in a bowl. Divide the rested dough into 6 meringues, open the meringues into long strips with your hands. Wrap two of the opened strips together and connect the ends. When there are 3 bagels, first dip them in molasses and then in sesame. Bake in a preheated 180 degree oven for 30 minutes. Enjoy your meal.

Mix yeast, salt, sugar and cold water in a bowl. Add flour little by little to the mixture and let it rest for 1 hour to ferment. Divide the fermented dough into 3 pieces. Open the meringues with your hands and fold each of them in half. After you have done all, leave them on the tray for 30 minutes. After the yeast process, scratch them with a knife. Bake them in a preheated 250 degree oven until they are golden brown. Bon appetit. Do not bake at lower temperatures, otherwise the breads will dry out.

Wash the figs and dry them all. Mix well the egg yolk, sugar, soda and flour. Let the mixture stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. In a separate bowl, whisk the egg whites and salt until fluffy. Slowly add to the flour mixture. Dip each of the figs into the mixture. Fry in hot oil and arrange on a paper towel to remove the oil. Take the finished ones on a serving plate and drizzle chocolate sauce on them. Bon appetit.

After whisking the yoghurt and egg in a bowl, add salt and baking powder. Gradually add flour to the mixture until you get a non-sticky consistency. Let the dough rest for ten minutes. After resting, roll out a medium-thick dough with the help of a rolling pin. Cut round dough with the help of a water glass. Put the oil in the pan and make sure it is hot. Throw the bagels in the hot oil and fry them both sides and back. Bon appetit.

Take the oil in the pan and fry the semolina on low heat for 5 minutes. Add the pine nuts and fry for another 2 minutes. Add milk, molasses and water to hot and mix. Wait for 15 minutes for it to absorb all the liquid. Enjoy your meal. Make sure that the stove is on low heat. Make sure to roast the semolina until it turns slightly dark, as the color will lighten when you add milk.

Take the yeast in a bowl and add 3 cups of warm water. Mix until the yeast dissolves. Then add sugar, salt, olive oil and flour and knead until it reaches a non-sticky consistency. Close the container, wait for it to ferment for 1 hour. After 1 hour, take the dough that has risen and divide it into 3 equal parts. Roll each piece into an oval shape with a rolling pin. Shape the dough with your fingertips and place each one on the baking tray. Before sending the pitas to the oven, spread the whipped yogurt on top. Bake in a preheated 240 degree oven for 30 minutes. Bon appetit.

Extract the stems and leaves of the cranberries and wash them in plenty of water. Put the cleaned cranberries in a deep pot and add 1.5 liters of hot water and boil them on low heat. After boiling, cook for 15-20 minutes. At this stage, you can optionally add 2 cloves. Pass the softened cranberries through a fine-mesh strainer or a clean cheesecloth. Add powdered sugar to the watery mixture that you have filtered and mix it well for the last time with a wooden spoon. Cool the cranberry sherbet you have prepared in the refrigerator. Enjoy your meal.

Wash the cranberries and put them in the pot. Transfer the granulated sugar and water to the pot. Cook on low heat until the cranberries are soft. After cooking, remove from the heat and transfer the seeds through a strainer and mash with a fork. Take the seedless parts of the cranberries back into the pot and add the cinnamon stick. Cook the cranberry until it thickens, add the lemon juice and remove the cinnamon. Enjoy your meal.

Take almond flour, flaxseed meal, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Mix all the dry ingredients. Add the eggs one by one and continue mixing. Add 200 ml of water and mix. Pour the olive oil last and mix for the last time. Oil your mold and pour the mortar. Bake in the preheated oven for 35 minutes. Bon appetit.

Grate the tomatoes, finely chop the hot peppers and cut the peppers into three. Mix the ingredients except the parsley in the bowl. At this stage, you should wait half an hour for the salt to dissolve. Divide the mixture into jars and place the parsley before closing the lid. Leave for 15 days in a cool place out of the sun. Bon appetit. If you prefer rock salt while preparing pickles, you will get a more delicious taste.

Wash wheat or cracked wheat and boil for 15 minutes. Take the butter in the pan and fry the sliced ​​green beans. You can add optional tomatoes at this stage. Add the vermicelli, then the bulgur and continue frying. Add the salt and fry for 2 more minutes. Add the boiled cracked wheat or cracked wheat. Add 1 liter of boiling water and leave it to cook for 20 minutes. Enjoy your meal. You can choose cracked wheat instead of cracked wheat.

Pull the raw almonds with the help of a rondo. When it comes to a large consistency, separate 3 tablespoons, and grind the rest until it reaches the consistency of flour. Roast 1 glass of flour and almonds in a pan until they turn brown. Put it in a mixing bowl and wait until it cools down a bit. Add 1 cup of powdered sugar, flour, butter, baking powder, vanilla to the almond and flour mixture. You will sprinkle the remaining powdered sugar on it in the last step. Knead all the ingredients thoroughly. Take the dough between two greaseproof papers and roll it out with the help of a rolling pin. When the dough thickness reaches 1 cm, cut it into a moon shape with the help of a glass. Bake in a preheated 170 degree oven for 20 minutes. Dip the cookies you took out of the oven into 1 glass of powdered sugar and serve. .

Mix oat paste, egg, yoghurt and salt well in a bowl. Put oiled paper in the toaster and pour the mixture. After cooking for a while, place the cheddar cheese between it and fold it in half. After the cheddar cheese melts, you can serve it. Enjoy your meal. You can add olives, depending on your preference. .

Mix warm water, oil, sugar, vanillin and flour in a bowl. Keep kneading until it becomes non-sticky. Cover the dough and let it rest for 20 minutes. Flour the counter and take the dough to the counter. Make 16 equal pieces from the rolled dough. Roll out each meringue thinly with a rolling pin and fold in each one by putting 1 tablespoon of chocolate cream. Cut the remaining parts of the dough with scissors. Bake in a fan oven set at 20 degrees for 6 minutes.
